title: ore-ida potato bake
directions: Thaw frozen potatoes and put into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Mix together soup, sour cream, onion and Cheddar cheese; add to potatoes.
Combine butter and the bread crumbs; cover top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: southern pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks, one at a time.
Add extract.
Dredge fruit and nuts with 2 cups flour.
Then add other 2 cups to mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Let sit overnight.
Keep covered tightly.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours. Makes 2 loaves.
Put pan of water in oven while baking cakes to make cakes moist.

title: chicken with leeks
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 400°
for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Simmer 10 minutes.
Chop the crawfish and mix with seasoning. Simmer 15 minutes. Bake one pie shell until light brown.
Pour mix in pie shell. Cover with other shell. Brush top of shell with melted butter.
Bake until golden brown. Freezes good!

title: french bread pizza
directions: In a medium skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and mushrooms; set aside.
Cut bread in half lengthwise and spread with the meat sauce.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with mozzarella.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Use whatever pizza toppings you have on hand and fix this different ways.

title: taco dip
directions: In mixing bowl, place cream cheese and mix until soft with fork.
Then fold in sour cream and mix together.
(Mixture will be lumpy.)
Fold onto dinner size plate or tray and spread evenly to edges.
Then layer:
tomatoes, onion and green pepper on top. Next pour entire bottle of taco sauce over vegetables.
Then garnish with grated cheese.
Serve with taco or tortilla chips.

title: syrup cake
directions: Stir in cinnamon or nutmeg.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350°. Cool in pan.

title: luncheon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients together with enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise twice its bulk. Make into rolls and place on a greased and floured pan and let rise.
Cook in preheated oven about 400° until browned.

title: brisket marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in oven roasting bag; soak 8 to 10 pound brisket 24 hours.
Drain, reserving 1 cup to pour over meat for cooking.
Bake 8 hours or larger brisket overnight at 250°.

title: veal cutlets fried(cotoletta fritto)
directions: This recipe for frying
veal cutlets is used in most of my recipes.
You
can
also
use
Boneless Chicken Breasts in place of
veal.
You
will find veal or chicken cooked in this manner to be fluffy and very moist.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tofu salad
directions: Break tofu into small pieces.
Boil water in a big pan.
Add tofu; bring to another boil and drain in a colander.
This is an easy way to squeeze out any excess water.

title: sherbet cooler punch
directions: Mix the 3 juices.
Put lemon juice, sugar and bananas in blender.
Puree.
Pour into juices.
Add sherbet and let melt. Pour into containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, mix with 7-Up and stir until slushy.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube cake pan.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together and slowly add to butter mixture until well blended.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Pour into prepared tube pan and bake one hour and twenty minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: reese's peanut butter treats
directions: Slice cookies into 1 inch rounds and divide each round into quarters.
Set one piece in each muffin tin of a small muffin tin pan (tart size).
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, until slightly puffy.
Immediately put one peanut butter cup on each cookie and press it down into the cookie.
Refrigerate until the shine is gone off of the chocolate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Stir to break up sausage.
Drain off fat.
Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake on cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Slowly heat 4-quart Dutch oven with tight fitting lid.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Heat, do not burn.
In hot butter over high heat, brown beef cubes well, using a fourth at a time or just enough to cover bottom of Dutch oven.
Lift out beef as it browns. Continue until beef is browned.
Add butter as needed.
Return beef to Dutch oven.
In small saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons brandy just until vapor rises.
Ignite; pour over beef.
As flame dies, remove beef.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to Dutch oven.
Heat slightly.
Add onions.
Cook over low heat, covered, until onions brown slightly. Add mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, meat extract paste and tomato paste until well blended. Stir in Burgundy, sherry, Port and broth.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bring wine mixture just to boiling, stirring.
Remove from heat. Add beef, pepper and bay leaf.
Mix well.
Bake, covered, stirring occasionally, 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add remaining brandy, little by little.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast sandwich
directions: Spray small bowl (custard dish is perfect) with Pam.
Break egg into small bowl.
Puncture egg yolk with fork.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook in microwave approximately 40 seconds on High.
Allow to stand while preparing rest of sandwich.

title: martha's cranberry sauce
directions: Grind up fresh cranberries real fine.
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar. Let set overnight.

title: puffy hot cakes
directions: Makes enough for 2.
Double recipe for 4.

title: celebration salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir until well mixed. Let set, stirring often until sugar is dissolved. Gently mix cauliflower, broccoli and tomatoes, coating all vegetables well with sauce. Cover. Put in refrigerator until cold. Mix again, coating all vegetables just before serving.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Dissolve this into 1/4 cup hot water and add to mayonnaise and lemon juice. Then add tuna, chopped celery, peas and chopped onion.
Stir well and place in a large casserole dish.
Let congeal overnight.
I always double this for a luncheon.

title: spicy zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans with shortening and flour.
In a large bowl, mix next 6 ingredients. Stir until blended; make a well in center of mixture.
In a separate medium bowl, combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir shredded zucchini into moist batter.
Pour batter into well of dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Spoon mixture into 2 prepared pans for 10 minutes.
Then remove from pans and serve.
Yields 2 loaves (16 servings each loaf).
Each serving contains 171 calories (43% from fat).

title: mock marzipan
directions: Soak the beans for 24 hours, then cook until tender in fresh, unsalted water.
Put them on a tin in a warm oven to get dry and floury.
Rub them through a sieve.
Beat the sugar into the bean puree; add the ground rice, warmed margarine and, finally, the flavouring.
Beat until smooth.
Any flavouring or colouring matter may be added.
(GR)

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Add salad dressing.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour and brown slightly.
Add drained corn and sour cream.
Mix; pour into small casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bacon bits.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave High 5 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Microwave High 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until foamy. Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Use the chicken broth to cook the rice. Saute celery, onion and garlic in butter. Combine soups, water and cheese. Combine cooked rice and cooked broccoli. In a 9 x 13 pan, put the broccoli and rice, then the chicken, then the sauce. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix with hands. Mixture will be thick.
Do not use mixer!
Now that mixture is mixed, put in a pan and smooth out to desired thickness.
Place in refrigerator to keep cool.

title: country-style chicken and dumplings
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat vegetable oil; add chicken.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently until golden brown.
Add garlic, onions and mushrooms; cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently until vegetables are tender.
Remove mixture to bowl; keep warm.
In same skillet over medium heat, melt butter or margarine, add flour; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture is golden brown.
Add instant chicken broth; gradually stir in 3 cups of water; cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.
Add carrots and peas to skillet along with chicken and vegetables; bring to boil, covered.

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt margarine, add sugar and milk.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and mints, stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Add vanilla, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour into greased pan or pan lined with foil and sprayed with cooking spray.

title: butterscotch nut bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients to the eggs in order given.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage spaghetti delight
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper in a large skillet over medium heat until sausage is brown, stirring to crumble meat. Drain well.
Return sausage mixture to skillet; add remaining ingredients.
Cook and cover over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 25 to 30 minutes or until spaghetti is done.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: classic lasagna
directions: In a large, heavy pan, lightly brown ground beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, parsley, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Saute yellow onion, garlic and green onions in olive oil until just tender.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: creamy cauliflower or broccoli soup
directions: Cook cauliflower or broccoli, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and chop into coarse pieces.
Set aside.
Cook onions in butter until tender.
Blend in the flour.
Stir in broth, milk and the Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly.
Add cooked vegetable.
Bring to a boil; stir in cheese until it melts.
Garnish with snipped chives or onion tops.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake as directed on box.
Top with:

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar with cream of tartar and salt.
Fold in vanilla.
Cut and fold in flour, adding a small amount at a time.
Turn into Bundt cake pan.
Cut through batter to remove bubbles.
Bake 60 minutes at 350° or until done.
Remove from oven and invert pan for one hour.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix tuna, mayonnaise, celery, cheese and onion well.
Spread buns with margarine.
Spread tuna mixture between halves of buns.
Wrap each burger in foil.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Dip cauliflower into egg, roll in crumbs and fry in deep hot fat (380°) until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sherry's famous cheese ball
directions: Let cheese set at room temperature (about 30 minutes).
Then cut green onions in small pieces.
Cut beef in small pieces.
Then mix well with your hands.
Roll into a ball, cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
Also, it's for all occasions.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, and boil for 30 minutes, stirring every few minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place pizza crust on sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart jar; shake well and refrigerate until ready to use as a basting sauce for barbecue chicken, beef or pork.
Yields approximately 1 cup sauce.

title: kid mix
directions: Mix and bag.
Mom will let you make it and you can eat it anytime because it's healthy.
*Any favorite cereal can be used.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for one minute.
Pour into 2 pie plates.
Grease and flour.
Sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and Karo syrup, creaming constantly. Add salt to eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken livers creole
directions: Coat a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Add oil and place over medium high heat until hot.
Add chicken livers and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until browned, stirring well.
Transfer livers to a bowl, using a slotted spoon.
Cook onion, celery and green peppers in skillet over medium-low heat until softened, stirring often.
Stir in flour and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken livers and next 8 ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over hot cooked regular rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashion bean soup(slow cooker)
directions: Soak beans in water overnight. Drain off the soaking water and discard. Combine all the ingredients in the slow cooker. Cover and cook 8 to 9 hours. Remove bone. Cut meat into bite size pieces and return to soup and stir well.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cool and pick meat from bones. Reserve broth.
Mix two soups and milk with chicken in bowl. Mix in different bowl the dressing, margarine and broth.

title: tuna and macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni as label directs; drain and cut broccoli into spears.
In covered 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 1-inch boiling water, cook broccoli 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Preheat oven to 350°.

In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat into hot butter, stir flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg until blended. Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Stir in lemon juice.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, stir in macaroni and tuna.
Arrange broccoli on top.
Pour sauce over casserole.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot.

title: dutch milk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar, adding milk slowly until well mixed. put into 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: curried chicken
directions: Mix onion, garlic and spices in bowl. Add 2 to 3 teaspoons water to make a paste.

Heat oil in frying pan. Add paste and cook 15 seconds, then add chicken. Turn chicken to get it covered with paste and cook until chicken is cooked through. Add boiling water and tomato paste. Cook about 15 minutes until sauce thickens a little. Serve over cooked rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix with hands into loose balls about the size of a small walnut.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 130 balls.

title: our favorite frosting
directions: Using mixer, combine all ingredients slowly at first, then add enough milk to get a spreadable mix.
Makes enough frosting for 2 (8-inch) cakes.

title: cornbread beef pie
directions: Cook onion in oil until transparent.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Add salt, pepper, mushrooms, tomato soup, milk and catsup.
Pour into greased 2-quart shallow casserole.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together; roll into 1 to 2-inch balls.
Brown in oil.

title: chicken boursin(creamy cheese filling)
directions: Divide cheese into 4 parts and spread on middle of each breast.
Roll breast around cheese.
Dip roll in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish, seam side down.
Cover with melted butter. Bake 20 to 30 minutes, basting occasionally, at 350°.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine with 3 1/2 Milky
Way candy bars. Add 2 cups sugar. Add eggs beating one at a time.
Add buttermilk alternating with flour, soda, vanilla and nuts. Mix all ingredients good and pour into two greased and floured nine inch cake pans. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice and water in shallow bowl (2-quart baking dish).
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix to blend thoroughly with pastry blender; cut in softened butter, resemble coarse crumbs.
Mix in nuts.
Crumble over apples.
(Don't pack.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Brown lightly.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Cut up	chicken; put in 6 quart pot.
Cover with water. Add whole, peeled onion, celery tops and salt to taste.
Bring to boil; spoon residue from water. Remove chicken, debone, cut up and return
to water. Add peeled and sliced carrot, sliced celery, chicken bouillon and Accent.

title: mexican corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Mix all ingredients together with mayonnaise and chill until ready to serve.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt.
Place in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Top each chop with 1 onion slice, 1 lemon slice, 1 tablespoon of brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of ketchup.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, spooning sauce over chops occasionally until done.

title: crispy vegetable salad
directions: Slice the celery.
Chop the green pepper and onion.
Drain all canned vegetables and combine.
In a saucepan, mix the sugar, white vinegar, vegetable oil, water and salt.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Chill.

title: casserole chilies rellenos
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish (glass is best). Arrange chilies in a layer over bottom of the dish, cover with cheese.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: With butter in large pan, saute onion and celery until soft. Add soup, milk and cheese; stir and cook until cheese is melted. Add broccoli and rice; mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish. Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tennessee hots(not for the faint-hearted!)
directions: Combine pickles, sugar and Tabasco sauce in gallon jar.
Store 3 days, periodically inverting jar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Pour oil into mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together. Alternate dry ingredients and eggs, one at a time, until all are used up.
Add nuts and carrots; mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Makes 2 or 3 layers.
Frost.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter and egg in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.

title: strawberry surprise cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with marshmallows.
Pour cake batter over marshmallows.
Mix Jell-O powder with strawberries, pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Strawberries go to bottom and marshmallows come to top!)
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in greased casserole bowl.
Top with dollops of sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: self frosting german chocolate cake
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as on package.
Pour over top of pecans and coconut.
Melt the stick of margarine and cream cheese together. Stir in 1 box confectioners sugar.
Pour over top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Lightly grease pan.
Lay 1 piece of dry beef on pan for each piece of chicken.
Put 1 slice of cheese and 1/2 strip bacon on top of each piece of chicken.
Pour soup and sour cream mixed over chicken.
Bake 3 to 5 hours at 250° or 3 hours at 275°.

title: fat-free raspberry jam bars
directions: Cream applesauce and brown sugar.
Combine flour, soda, salt and oats; stir into creamed mixture.
Press half of mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread jam on crust and spread remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients except olives.
Take 1 tablespoon of dough and mold around an olive.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
This is a good hors d'oeuvre for a party.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Boil spaghetti in leftover chicken broth and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a deep dish casserole dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: olive cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop olives.
Mix all ingredients together and form ball.
Sprinkle on parsley flakes.

title: dixie pie
directions: Mix in bowl in order given and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes its own top.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients, nuts and pineapple.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 365° for 15 minutes or when cookie springs back when pressed with fingers.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onion and pepper in a little olive oil.
Add the tomatoes, herbs and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: cheese-rice crispy
directions: Mix grated cheese and margarine.
Add flour and work together well with hands.
Add cereal and mix.
Shape into small balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: holiday ribbon salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve lime gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Add 2 cups cold water. Stir. Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour. In a bowl, dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in marshmallows until melted. Cool for 20 minutes. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Gradually beat in lemon gelatin. Stir in pineapple. Carefully spoon over the lime layer. Chill until set. Dissolve cherry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Add the remaining cold water; stir. Spoon over the lemon layer. Refrigerate overnight. Cut into squares. May serve on lettuce leaves. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: lemon cake
directions: Fix as directed on box.
Put in three 9-inch cake pans.
Cook at 350° until light brown.

title: roast shell steak au jus
directions: Brush meat with melted butter or margarine.
Place meat on rack in small roasting pan and roast in oven 25 to 30 minutes for rare, 35 to 40 minutes for medium.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place meat on carving board, let rest for 1 minute before carving.
Discard all but 1 teaspoon of drippings from pan. Place pan over low heat.
Add bouillon, stirring up brown bits. Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Place in gravy boat.
Carve meat across grain.
Serve with gravy.
Serves 2.
Good with baked potato and marinated broccoli.

title: old time fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, milk, salt and corn syrup.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves and chocolate melts to boiling.
Then cook to soft ball stage (234°), stirring only if necessary. Immediately remove from heat.
Add butter and cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fudge thickens and starts to lose its gloss; spread in buttered shallow pan.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except the chocolate and nuts). Spread onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes. While still hot, place chocolate bars on top to melt.
When melted, sprinkle nuts over.
Let cool and slice into bars.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Combine cereal, sugar, salt, margarine and boiling water, then cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let sit until it foams. Combine yeast mixture with cereal mixture, egg and flour.
Mix until stiff dough has formed.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Grease bowl.
Put dough in bowl; set in warm place. Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; form small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet close together.
Brush with butter.
Let rise 1 hour, covered.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then mix 1/2 of each grated cheese with cream cheese mixture and top with remaining grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in baking dish.
Serve with chips.

title: lightning microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in medium glass bowl. Microwave at High power for 2 to 3 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Perfect every time!
And so easy!

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Skin chicken breast.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Dip chicken in butter and coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Have cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Mix together well. Add flour and mix.
Add Rice Krispies and mix easily so that you don't mash all of them.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown, about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch stew
directions: Add last 4 ingredients to beans and cook until done.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and cool.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs and stir into cooled oatmeal.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to batter.
Stir in nuts (optional). Pour into greased and floured 9 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve package of jello with 1 cup hot water.
Divide mixture in half.
Use 1/2 of mixture and add 3 tablespoons cold water.
(Save other 1/2 cup of jello.)
Pour mixture with cold water in a 9 x 13-inch pan (or whatever size you want).
Let this set until firm.
When firm, take remaining 1/2 cup of jello and add 1/3 cup sour cream and mix well.
Then pour over plain layer and let set well.
Repeat this process until you have achieved thickness you desire.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Set aside. In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Alternately add flour mixture with milk just until blended, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in bananas and nuts. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely. Makes 1 loaf.

title: smashing squash
directions: Cube
squash, dice onion.
Steam squash and onion until just crisp-tender.
Break up pieces with a fork.
Do not stir. Fold
in melted
butter
and
sour cream.
Add 2/3 crumbs and flavor packet
from Stove Top stuffing.
Pour into a buttered casserole. Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetarian vermicelli
directions: Stir-fry red and green peppers until crisp-tender.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add hominy and beans.
Cook until heated through.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook about 5 minutes.
In large kettle, cook pasta 5 to 7 minutes until tender.
Drain and transfer to a large platter.
Top with cheese mixture.
Toss and serve at once.
Yields 4 main dish servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine or butter and add onions.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Chop broccoli and add along with chicken broth. Cook until the broccoli is tender, about 45 minutes.
Cook slowly. Then add milk and let heat, before adding approximately 3/4 pound Velveeta cheese.
Stir while the cheese melts.
It's done...but better if soup sits for awhile.
No salt.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray a 2-quart oblong dish with vegetable cooking spray. Arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine soup and water; spoon over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Serve with pasta.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Heat oil in frypan; saute tomatoes, onions and garlic about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover; simmer tomatoes in their own juices about 20 minutes.
Strain through sieve; return puree to frypan.
Cook until liquid is reduced to two-thirds; stir frequently.
Set aside.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In a large bowl, marinate chicken with first three ingredients for at least 1 hour.
In a smaller bowl, prepare batter with eggs, cornstarch and baking powder.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Dip chicken in batter and fry until golden brown.
Remove and cool before slicing into 1 1/2-inch strips.
In a saucepan, heat chicken broth, cornstarch, salt and lemon juice.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Pour sauce over chicken and garnish with lemon slices.

title: potato stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Filling will set more while cooling.

title: holiday potatoes for the crowd
directions: Prepare ahead 24 hours.
Cool and grate the skinned potatoes. Saute the onions in 1/3 cup butter.
Add celery soup, grated cheese and sour cream.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in greased large casserole baking dish.
Top with sprinkled crushed cornflakes and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and make a hole in center.
Pour in rest of ingredients and mix until smooth.
Bake in 3 loaf pans (well-greased) for 1 hour at 350°.
Chopped pecans may be added to batter.

title: purple cow(for kids)
directions: Blend in blender and serve.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash, adding milk and butter as needed. Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Add cheese to potatoes and beat with mixer. Saute onions in butter until tender. Add 1/3 of the butter and onion mixture to potatoes.
Add salt to taste.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with 1/2 of the noodles, then 1/2 of the potatoes.
Repeat, ending with noodles.
Pour the remaining butter and onions over top of noodles.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn and rice salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine corn, rice, pepper, olive and onion. Combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce and parsley.
Pour over corn mixture.
Cover and chill. (Can use dressing you buy from store.)

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thoroughly rinse wild rice.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve chicken bouillon in boiling water and pour over rice.
Cover pan tightly, put into oven and turn off. Leave overnight.
Drain off any liquid left.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: john's pecan pie(won 1st place in 4h bake-off in 1974 at age 10)
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add shortening.
Add water and make down.
Don't mix too much.

title: sausage pecan dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery and celery tops in butter.
Cook sausage in separate skillet.
Add salt, pepper and thyme to bread crumbs. Add crumb mixture to skillet with vegetables.
Drain sausage.
Add sausage to vegetable mixture.
Add more melted butter if needed. Taste for seasoning.
Add pecans.
Makes enough for 10 pound bird.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy. Gradually add sugar; beat until fluffy. Add egg; beat until light and fluffy. Blend in vanilla. Gradually add flour to creamed mixture; blend well. Stir in oats. Chill dough.

Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on board or canvas which has been lightly coated with xxx sugar. Cut into desired shapes with floured cookie cutters. Place on buttered cookie sheets. Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet immediately with metal spatula; cool on wire racks. Decorate with xxx frosting and red and green candied cherries.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain grease.
In roasting pan, mix all other ingredients well.
Place Tater Tots on top. Bake for 1 hour at 375° without cover.
Great as a passing dish at functions or you can use 1/2 ingredients for the family.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Place rice in 12-cup casserole and sprinkle in sugar.
Mix in milk and lemon rind.
Cover and microwave 18 minutes at Medium-high, stirring twice.
Add raisins, cream, fruit and cinnamon; mix well.
Continue microwaving 19 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Add egg, mix well and finish microwaving 2 minutes at low, uncovered.
Serve plain or drizzled with maple syrup.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making two 8-inch layers. Split both layers (when cool) horizontally.
Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Spread all but 1 cup of the sour cream mixture between the four layers.
Blend the remaining sour cream with whipped cream and spread on top and sides of cake. Seal in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: biscuit islands
directions: Pan-fry burger with sauces added.
Lay out biscuits on baking sheet.
Scoop burger over top.
Cook for approximately 12 minutes, then lay a slice of cheese over each one and bake 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: banana punch for 50
directions: Combine 8 cups water with 4 cups sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 15 minutes and cool.
Add other ingredients, except ginger ale. Mix thoroughly and freeze.
Remove from freezer 4 hours before serving time.
Add ginger ale at serving time.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter, milk and peanut butter in saucepan and boil 1 minute.
After it starts to boil, remove from stove and add vanilla.
Add oats.
Stir until all the oats are colored.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Cream butter and 1/3 cup sugar until light and fluffy; blend in 1 egg.
Add flour, mixing well.
Spread dough on bottom and 2 inches on sides of 9-inch spring form pan.
(I use a pie pan.) Bake at 400 degrees for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Lower oven temperature to 350 degrees.

title: artichoke hearts
directions: Sprinkle Parmesan cheese into the hearts.
Mix together and heat in microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers or any chips.

title: apple streudel
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening until the size of peas.
Add sugar; cut again.
Add eggs that are slightly beaten.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet with a rim, 3/4 of the ingredients.
Cover with applesauce.
Add remaining ingredients on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.

title: terri's yeast bread
directions: Water should be warm (not hot) to dissolve and activate the yeast.
Add yeast, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add 5 cups flour and mix well.
Add remaining flour; mix well and add the oil.
Knead slightly.
Cover with a towel; let rise (in a warm, draftless place) to double its size.
Knead or punch down, shape into rolls or loaves and let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour for rolls and approximately 45 minutes for loaves.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into a ball.
Roll in 1/4 cup finely chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate covered bananas
directions: You will need 12 to 16 wooden sticks.

title: rhubarb soft pie
directions: Cook until thick over low heat.
Bake crust, then pour in filling.
Cover meringue, using 3 egg whites.
Bake until brown.

title: spiced chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream shortening, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until light.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Beat until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into pans and bake for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand for at least 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: fried okra
directions: Pour milk over okra.
Mix flour, corn meal, salt and pepper. Put flour mixture in bag or bowl with cover.
Put small amount of okra in at a time and shake to coat.
Deep fry and drain.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars and margarine. Add eggs, vanilla and honey. Blend in flour, oatmeal and salt and soda. Stir in coconut and chips. Bake at 325° on greased cookie sheet.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix well; chill and serve.
Recipe can be cut in half or doubled!
Super quick and good!

title: granny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar, walnuts and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped nuts (mixed together).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While warm, poke holes with a fork.
Pour on one can Eagle Brand milk.
Let cool.

title: kolacky
directions: Scald, cream and cool.
Add yeast and sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut butter into flour as for pie crust.
Add salt, yeast mixture and egg yolks to flour mixture.
Stir and beat to form smooth soft dough.
Cover tightly and let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with round 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make indentations in center and fill with fruits.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown.
Remove from cookie sheet to cooling rack.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chess bars
directions: With electric mixer, beat together cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Mixture will be thick.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam vegetable spray.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken
covered
in water for about 20 minutes or until done.
Cut
into
bite-size
pieces.
Combine the soups, spices, broth,
tomatoes
with
green
chilies and the onions. Grease a 3-quart casserole and line it with Doritos.
Arrange the chicken on
Doritos.
Sprinkle
with 1 cup of the cheese, then pour the soup mixture on and top with rest of the cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp for two
directions: Place apples and water in 2 to 2 1/2 cup shallow baking dish. Combine dry ingredients. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: wild turkey jerky(food dehydrator needed for this recipe.)
directions: Slice turkey across the grain in 1 inch strips, about 1/4 inch thick.
(Meat will cut easier if partially frozen.)
Take all your fixins' and mix'em up.
Pour'em over the turkey slices.
Make sure all your turkey gets a fair amount on it.
Place turkey on trays in single layer in dehydrator and dry overnight.
When the rooster crows, your turkey will be jerky.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Dip chicken in eggs, then bread crumbs.
Mix some butter, chives and garlic together (however you like to taste).
Take 1 tablespoon of mixture and put on chicken.
Roll chicken up and place a toothpick in it to hold.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes or until crispy brown on a cookie sheet.

title: easy english toffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and allow to come to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add cut almonds and cook until nuts are a light brown in color.
Pour into pan.
Pour melted chocolate over surface and cover with finely ground walnuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1 cup nuts) in bowl.
Shape with hands into a ball and refrigerate overnight.
Then roll ball in the other cup of nuts.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: divinity(never fail)
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, salt and water together until a small amount forms a soft ball in water (soft ball on candy thermometer).

Take out 1/2 cup of mixture and pour slowly over beaten egg whites (they should have been beaten until stiff); continue beating slowly while remaining syrup cooks to hard ball stage on candy thermometer.
Beat rapidly while pouring remaining syrup over egg white mixture.
When it begins to thicken, add nuts and vanilla and beat by hand until candy holds shape when dropped by spoon.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all except 7Up.
Freeze.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, set our until slushy when ready to serve.
Pour 7Up over it. Makes about 40 cups.

title: ham & scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375. Mix all ingredients except cheese together, place ingredients in ungreased baking dish cover with foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove foil spread cheese on top and cook another 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed; add soup, milk and chicken.
Bake until bubbly in buttered casserole dish. Serves 5.

title: corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Combine milk with eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Add shortening and stir until blended.
Pour into breadstick pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: devil's float
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch flat pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix like cake and drop by spoonfuls in hot syrup.
Bake.

title: new orleans gumbo
directions: In a large heavy skillet, fry bacon, sausage and chicken gizzards until lightly brown. With a slotted spoon, dip out of skillet, leaving the drippings. Place bacon, sausage and gizzards in a large kettle.

title: mildred's chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing and margarine; place half in casserole dish. Combine chicken, soups and broth.
Pour into dish.
Put remaining dressing on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into small balls or rolls.
Drop into deep fat and fry until golden brown.

title: curried rabbit
directions: Boil rabbit with salt.
Cool and separate from bone.
Fry meat in butter until brown.
Add onions and carrots and simmer.
Add soup and milk.
Let simmer until meat is tender.
Add curry powder to taste.
My favorite (if you like rabbit).

title: diabetic carrot cake
directions: Beat together eggs, butter and pineapple juice.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices. Beat well.
Stir in carrots.
Spread half the batter evenly in an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Mix all soup in a 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole dish.
Add water and rice.
Mix well.
Place chicken pieces skin side up in pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix all these together until it forms a pastry.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix all but cheese.
Shape them into 6 balls.
Cook 5 minutes on first side.
Turn.
Top with cheese.
Cook until done.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Stir dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Stir all well, then chill.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain canned salmon, saving liquid. Remove skin and bones.
Mix salmon in large bowl with bread cubes. Make white sauce by blending butter or margarine with flour over medium heat.
Add the 1 cup liquid and cook, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg, onion and seasonings; blend well.
Add the white sauce to the salmon and bread cubes; mix together well.
Place in a greased loaf pan; bake uncovered for one (1) hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no peek beef dish
directions: Place stew beef in baking dish.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Don't peek!
A good Sunday meal to cook while at church.

title: pumpkin pie filling
directions: Blend together and add milk.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 large or 4 small pies.

title: mocha frappe
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; blend at medium-low speed until smooth.
Pour into serving glasses.
Makes 4 servings.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture. Add vanilla.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of a small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add powdered sugar.
Whip cream, then add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Spoon pie filling on top and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread undrained pineapple over pie filling.
Crumble cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Place chopped nuts on butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to boil.
Add to all dry ingredients. Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into floured Pyrex dish and cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and put marshmallows on top.
Put back in oven until puffy.
Add pecans and ice while hot.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into balls. Dip in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes enough to break apart into bite size chunks, but not until mushy.
Mix together sour cream, soup, cheese, margarine and onions, then add potatoes.
Mix and put into a 13 x 9-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Blend well.
Stir in apples, nuts, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: one, two punch
directions: Freeze red Hawaiian Punch for two hours.
Add the can of frozen juice.
Float orange and lemon slices on top.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt in large bowl.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Pack in freezer containers (or butter bowls) leaving 1-inch space at top.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and dill. Pour into each container to cover.
Seal and freeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and shortening until it's like coarse meal.
In a small bowl, beat the egg, vinegar and water. Add this to the flour mixture; mix together into form of a ball. Divide into 5 little balls, enough to make 5 shells.
Can be refrigerated for a week or more if placed in plastic bag and sealed.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Saute oleo and onion. Mix sour cream, onion, butter, cheese, soup, salt and pepper. Add hash browns and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, slightly beat egg by hand.
Add sugar, sour cream, flour, vanilla and salt and mix. Stir in apples (peeled and sliced).
Pour in pie shell; bake for 30 minutes.

title: cottage meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine ketchup, salt, pepper, red pepper, eggs and bread crumbs.
Add ground beef.
Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
Press in the beef mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Saute the onions in the butter. Put in bottom of unbaked pie shell. Mix the eggs, salt, paprika and milk. Pour over onions and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix the ingredients well and chill.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef or turkey.
Drain.
In saucepan combine all ingredients, except tortilla chips and cheese.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.
Serve in bowls and sprinkle with cheese on top.
Serve with chips.

title: caesar bean salad
directions: Pour beans into bowl and add onion and cover with Caesar salad dressing.
Let set at least 2 hours.
Drain and put on lettuce leaf.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Save 1 cup of chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients.
Layer corn tortillas, torn in pieces, chicken mixture and grated cheese. Layer once again.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine 2 teaspoons butter, flour, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Place on heat.
Add sour cream gradually.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in beans.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and corn flakes, mixed with remaining margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: holiday fruit pie
directions: Fill pie crust with fruit in order given.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with rind.
Top with vented pie crust.
Pinch edges closed.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until fruit is tender.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crush pretzels; combine with granulated sugar and melted butter.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch oblong buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from cooked beans.
Toss all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: pineapple date whip
directions: Have cream chilled in refrigerator; turn into chilled bowl. Beat with chilled beater until thick.
Add lemon juice and beat until quite stiff.
Fold in pineapple, chopped dates and salt. Fold in sugar to suit taste.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise, and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks; stir in mayonnaise and next five ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes.
Put salt in these.
Drain well.
Grind cabbage, onions and peppers.
Do not drain these.
Mix sugar, vinegar and pickling spices (tie pickling spices in a piece of cheesecloth).
Put all ingredients together.
Cook until it changes color.
Do not overcook.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 18 pints. I buy about 4 pounds cabbage and onions to allow for peelings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over pretzel crust.
Make jello according to package directions and stir in thawed strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares to serve. Makes 20 to 24 squares.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Place diced chiles in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer 2 1/2 cups Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese on top of chiles.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Beat egg yolks, dry nonfat milk, water and flour together.
Fold in egg whites. Pour over chile-cheese layers.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve cold.
Add any other fruits of your choice.

title: quick and easy watermelon pie
directions: Fold together milk and topping.
Add lime juice.
Fold in watermelon balls, reserving about 5 for garnish.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Place remaining watermelon balls on pie to garnish.
Chill for 2 or more hours before serving.

title: german cucumber salad
directions: Let first 4 ingredients set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Drain salt from cucumber mixture. Pour sugar mixture over cucumbers. Chill 1 hour.
May be kept 3 months in fridge.
May be frozen in small container.

title: best lasagne
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Drain and keep in cold water. Brown meat and drain.
Add the onion; brown, then add the tomato sauce and tomatoes, garlic, sausage, basil and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix together the cottage cheese, eggs, pepper, 4 tablespoons parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Shred mild and Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside to layer mixture.
Layer cold noodles in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish, then spread on meat mixture, then cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle small amount of last 2 cheeses. Layer 3 layers and then large amount (sprinkle) of last 2 cheeses. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Will make 3 (13 x 9-inch) dishes with 3 layers.
Will freeze nicely if covered with Saran Wrap.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool. Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Add cooled raisins and water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture to raisin mixture; blend well and add nuts.
Chill dough, then drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes on cookie sheet before removing to cake racks.
Yield:
7 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, water and oil in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Mix all other ingredients.
Pour hot liquid over and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place butter in bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Place pan in oven to melt butter; meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add sugar, flour, milk and vanilla and stir thoroughly.
Remove pie pan from oven and tilt pan to cover bottom and sides with butter, pour excess butter into egg mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in coconut.
Pour mixture into pie pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: ham delights
directions: Chop ham and cheese and mix.
Melt margarine, mustard, poppy, onion and Worcestershire.
Slice rolls in half; spread margarine mixture on both sides of rolls.
Sprinkle ham and wrap in foil. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients real well.
Shape into ball or 2 small balls.
Roll completely in chopped pecans.
Freezes well.

title: caramel nut candy
directions: Mix all ingredients in a double boiler or very slowly on low heat.
While candy is cooling, prepare a large metal tray by covering it with waxed paper.
(Greasing the waxed paper slightly helps ensure the candies won't stick.)
Drop small tablespoons of the candy mix onto the wax paper.
Chill until firm and store in the refrigerator.
Chewy and delicious.

title: sauteed chicken breasts(portuguese)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken and brown lightly on both sides. Add wine and stir to loosen browned particles from the skillet.
Add artichokes.
Cover and simmer 12 minutes until chicken is firm and white.
Remove chicken to warm platter. Add sour cream to artichoke mixture and heat over low flame 1 minute; do not boil. Stir in bacon and parsley. Serve over chicken and accompany with wild rice.

title: oven "fried" salmon cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium sized bowl thoroughly combine all the ingredients except the vegetable oil spray and shape into 8 patties.
Place the patties on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with vegetable oil.
Put the sheet in the hot oven and bake the patties for 5 minutes or until they are golden on both sides.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef; dice onion.
Add to meat.
Let simmer.
Add chicken soup, catsup, mustard and Lea & Perrins.
Let simmer, stirring occasionally.
If bread is not cut, cut bread.
Put bread in oven.
Let brown on one side.
Take out and turn over.
Put ground beef mixture on top, then put cheese on.
Put back in oven until cheese starts to bubble.
Serve immediately.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer sausage in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add 1 cup grated cheese and the other ingredients.
Let stand all night in refrigerator.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook about 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
In skillet, cook medium onion in stick of margarine.
Then add chopped cheese until melted.
Turn off heat, add soup.
Pour all into casserole and top with crackers.
Bake until bubbly.

title: squash pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients well; put into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until pie is brown. Tastes like coconut pie!

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and fry.
Drain bacon and add to ingredients.
Cook in oven at 350° for 55 minutes.
Stir 1 cup cubed Cheddar cheese into cooked beans.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla until stiff.
Gradually add the sugar, beating well after each addition, so that sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Fold in gently the package of chocolate chips.
Drop by a teaspoon onto two large greased cookie sheets.
Place cookies in a preheated 375° oven.
Turn off oven and "LEAVE OVERNIGHT".
Do not open oven door for at least 8 hours if made during the day.
No peeking.

title: 'da best pie crust
directions: Mix all together.
Form and roll out between 2 layers of wax paper.
To put in a pie tin, lift off top layer of wax paper; put pie tin upside down on dough.
Flip over and remove wax paper. Form in pie tin as desired.

title: black cherry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in juices drained from fruits and heated to boiling.
Add cream cheese and mix all ingredients well.
Add Cokes last.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low sugar oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, Sugar Twin and dry milk.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add oats and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and then add dates and nuts.
Mix well and drop on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix onion, bell pepper and crackers into meat.
Add egg and catsup.
Put in loaf pan and pour catsup on top of meat.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Arrange lettuce, olives, onions, cucumber, tomatoes and cheese on a platter.
Mix olive oil, red wine vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over salad and serve.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: welsh griddle scones
directions: Rub fat into flour.
Add other ingredients and mix with milk or egg and milk to a pastry consistency.
Roll out and cut into rounds.
Heat griddle for 5 minutes.
Cook both sides at reduced heat.
Serve hot dusted with caster sugar or cold spread with butter.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, milk, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I set the pudding in another pan with about 1 inch of water to bake.
It forms a nice custard.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients and bring to a boil for about 3 - 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add last three ingredients and stir.
Spoon onto wax paper until cool.

title: pineapple cream icebox pie
directions: Bake the crust at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until the top edges start to turn brown, let cool to touch. Mix the drained crushed pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and the lemon juice together and pour immediately into the pie crust. Spread the Cool Whip on top. The mixture should set up when poured into the crust. If not, let it set in the refrigerator for awhile.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding small amount of water (3 tablespoons of water at a time) until mixture can be shaped into a ball (not sticky).
Let rise; cover with a dish cloth for about 30 minutes.
Roll out on floured table or countertop, turning dough over several times, until it is the size of 1 large cookie sheet. Push side down sides for crust.
Makes enough for a large pizza.

title: mussels and tubetti(a favorite from the ancient seaside city of bari, italy)
directions: Place mussels in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add the cool water, tablespoon of olive oil, 1/4 cup white wine and 1 clove of garlic, sliced finely.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat after the mussels open.
Strain the broth and reserve.
Remove the mussels from the shells and reserve them.
Strain the tomatoes, reserve the liquid.
Chop the tomatoes coarsely.

title: indiana chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and drain well. Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan and set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Dip chicken in evaporated milk and shake excess off.
Roll in dry mixture until coated well and place in baking pan.
Spoon melted butter or margarine over top of each piece.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hungry jack potatoes
directions: Fix Hungry Jack instant potatoes as directed on package for 12 servings.
Add about 1/2 cup extra flakes.
Add to this cream cheese and sour cream.
Pour into 2 (2-quart) casseroles.
Cover top with melted butter.
Sprinkle garlic salt, onion salt and lots of Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Form mixture into a ball and roll in nuts. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Mix milk and pudding together; add Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Crush cookies.
Layer with cream mixture.
Top with Oreo cookies.
Add gummy worms to very top.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well. Add oil, sugar and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well and add vanilla.
Grease two loaf pans or 1 tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Stir together flour, soda and baking powder. Stir together with remaining ingredients until well blended. Drop by tablespoon on hot greased grill.

title: fruit salad with a twist
directions: Combine fruit and lettuce in salad bowl.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Drizzle with olive oil.
May add croutons and red onion rings.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze until solid.
Spoon into glasses and cover with 7-Up.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix flour, pecans, sugar and vanilla together.
Melt margarine and add to mixture.
Add salt.
Shape like fingers and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: penne with ricotta and spinach sauce
directions: Chop spinach rather fine; set aside.
In a large skillet, put in 4 tablespoons butter; melt at medium-high.
After butter has melted, add spinach and a liberal 2 or 3 pinches of salt.
Saute spinach 2 minutes or so; turn frequently, then turn off heat. Cook pasta until al dente.
Drain.

title: quiche lorraine a la jeanne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat water in 12-inch or larger skillet over medium heat.
Add bacon and onions and cook, stirring frequently, until onions are very limp, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat to cool slightly.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, egg substitute, chives, salt and pepper.
Add cooled onion mixture and mix well.
Pour into partially baked crust and spread evenly. Sprinkle with caraway seed and bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes or until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mayme kotar's skillet date cookies
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add chopped dates, sugar and eggs.
Adjust heat to medium and stir constantly as the date mixture cooks for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add crispy rice cereal and chopped nutmeats.
Mix well.
Quickly shape into balls and flatten slightly.
Roll in coconut flakes, pressing lightly.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 or 4 weeks.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and place in greased casserole.
In a small saucepan, saute onion in butter until soft.
Add bread crumbs, seasonings.
Spoon onion mix on top of split tomatoes. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Pour over sliced tomatoes and onions.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Combine chicken, soups, onion and Ro-Tel and chicken broth.
Crush Doritos.
Put half of it on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then spread mixture on.
Then put on rest of Doritos.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cover with foil.

title: cloud topped peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy pan combine milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Bring to boil over moderate heat.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat:
Add morsels and stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Spread into 9 inch foil-lined pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: With adult help, preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with shortening.
Put butter and chocolate in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat on low until melted, stirring once or twice. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and eggs, one at a time until well mixed.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: In mixing bowl, place cream cheese and soup (do not dilute soup).
Mix with electric mixer.
Garnish with jalapeno peppers. Chill in refrigerator until time to serve.
Time: 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes. Cream together
butter,
sugars and eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture then dry ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: honey baked ham
directions: Bring butter, honey and syrup to a boil; keep hot, not boiling.
Trim fat off ham.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes and then baste with honey mixture every 15 minutes.
Bake ham about 1 1/2 hours.
Can be made day before and reheated.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Place cover on double boiler to keep out steam and keep in heat.
Takes about 20 minutes for these to melt; stir frequently.
Add peanuts, one cup at a time, stirring well after each addition.
The last addition makes a very stiff mixture.
When all nuts are well covered with the chocolate-butterscotch mixture, remove from heat and drop by teaspoon or half-teaspoon onto a wax paper covered cookie sheet. Refrigerate.
(Takes several cookie sheets.)
These will become solid in a couple of hours.

title: stuffed green bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Wash and lightly salt inside of peppers.
While cooking rice, brown hamburger and onion in a large skillet.
Season with salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cooked rice, tomato sauce and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
Stuff peppers full and top with rest of the tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until peppers are very tender.

title: anytime bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs and mix.
Add cereal and bran.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This is a very large recipe and may be cut in half.

title: momo welch's yeast rolls
directions: Beat dough and add about 5 cups flour and knead in large bowl until stiff.
Place in bowl and cover and let rise again (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Grease pans with cooking oil and pinch off and roll dough into balls.
Cover and let rise double their size.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until well blended. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: egg sausage bake
directions: Cut bread into cubes or triangles and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown and thoroughly drain pork sausage.
Spoon over bread, then sprinkle Cheddar over top.
Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Best when put together the night before. Refrigerate and cook the next morning.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until chicken is completely done. Cut cabbage in half and shred; may also be chopped for finer texture. Chop chicken and onions and add to cabbage mixture. May be refrigerated overnight, if desired. Add noodles with chicken mixture and sesame seeds just before serving. Mix salad with dressing and serve with crackers.

title: laura osgood bean's sourdough bread
directions: Combine yeast, milk, sugar and salt.
Let stand until foamy. Add sourdough starter.
Combine with flour; knead until shiny.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Shape into loaves; let rise.
Brush tops with mixture of slightly beaten egg white and water.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.

title: blarney stones
directions: Cream frosting ingredients together.
Ice all sides and roll in crushed salted peanuts.	Makes 1/2 pound.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine limeade, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Pour the entire mixture over ice cubes.
A sprig of mint or bits of maraschino cherries may be added.
Makes 75 servings.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and melted chocolate.
Add to sugar and butter; add vanilla.
Add 1 egg and beat for 3 minutes.
Add the other egg and beat for 3 more minutes.
This is very important to beat for exactly the same time.
Pour into pie shell and top with Cool Whip (and sprinkles if desired).

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in flavorings and nuts.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: homemade chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add cocoa and stir over med. heat for a minute or two.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar a little at a time, adding a little bit of hot water when it gets thick. Continue until all sugar is used.
Beat a few strokes until desired consistency.
Add pinch of salt and 1 t. vanilla.
Use about half of the above for one layer cake.
Also add nuts if desired.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburg; crumble with spatula as it fries.
Drain.
Add diced green pepper and diced onion.
Saute until tender.
Add enough ketchup to create a sauce (may add some water if you like it saucier).
Add about a teaspoon of prepared mustard and sugar to taste.
Serve hot on buns with or without American cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with the other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with 2 cans of onion rings and bake 10 minutes or more until casserole is hot.
This makes 2 casseroles.

title: hot marinated mushrooms
directions: Layer mushrooms in 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Heat remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over the mushrooms and bake uncovered at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: banana split muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix and 1/4 cup sugar.
In a small bowl, combine egg yolks, milk and butter.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine flour, oats, coconut, wheat germ, Grape-Nuts and chopped nuts in a large bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Stir into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: st. louis noodles
directions: Saute the ground beef, onions and peppers.
Add the mushrooms, if desired.
Add the soup and water. Cook the noodles; drain. Add to rest of the ingredients. Add the cheese. Cover with foil and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, green pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Good with crackers or can be used for finger sandwiches.

title: bobbie's baked beans
directions: Dry chicken well. Season both sides with Accent, Lawry's salt, salt and pepper.
Let stand 3/4 hour.
Flour and let stand 15 minutes.
Beat 1 egg slightly and add a little water. Dip and roll in bread crumbs.
Grease cookie sheet well. Brush chicken with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, skin up.

title: chestnut dressing
directions: Partially cook celery and onions in water to cover. Add butter to melt.
Mix all ingredients well in order given.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch oiled baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve while warm.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.
(No water is used in Jell-O.)

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Whip milk and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and place over crust.
Chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Simmer onion soup mix in 2 cups of water.
Pour soup mix over 1 cup of rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Cover with 2 cans of mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yam pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix all ingredients except cream; pour into dish.
Bake until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serve with cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese style hash
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, celery, mushroom and cream of chicken soups and warm water.
Stir in rice, sprouts, soy sauce and pepper. Place in lightly greased casserole.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Cover mixture with the noodles and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased Pam sprayed pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
In separate bowl, mix together egg, onion and buttermilk.
Stir into dry ingredients until blended. Add jalapenos (if desired).
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot deep fat (370°) and fry about 1 minute each side, or until golden, turning to brown both sides.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients; sift in a bowl the sugar and flour.
Combine the two mixtures; add the eggs, sour milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well and bake in a jelly roll pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: smoked beef dip with olives
directions: Soak onion in sherry or white wine.
Add softened cream cheese, mayonnaise or salad dressing, smoked beef and stuffed olives.
Mix well and chill.
Serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: pat's vegetable soup
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and bring to boil.
Add 1 cup macaroni and top with water.
Heat 15 minutes and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Break up cranberry sauce with a fork and add package of Jell-O (dry).
Add 1 cup boiling water and combine.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Mix and chill.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, M&Ms, and peanuts in a large bowl.
In a pan, heat marshmallows and butter until melted.
Pour over popcorn mixture and mix well.
Pour into your pan and let set until cool. Turn onto serving place.
Slice, eat, and enjoy.

title: edible eights
directions: Roll each biscuit into a 9-inch rope.
Form each rope into a circle and pinch the ends together with your fingers.
Dip each circle into melted butter and then into the mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Then, twist each circle into a figure eight.
Place on a well greased cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes. Serve warm.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Outline casserole dishes with Cool Whip.
Spread peanut butter on crackers.
Line bottom of dish with crackers, then layer of Cool Whip and then layer of syrup.
Repeat another layer of each. Top with Hershey's syrup.

title: fried rice
directions: If using fresh shrimp, remove shell, devein and clean shrimp. If using frozen, defrost and drain; set aside.
Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil in a wok or large skillet.
Add beaten eggs and scramble over medium heat.
Remove from wok or skillet; cover and set aside. Add 1/2 more tablespoon oil and fry shrimp for 8 minutes if raw and 4 minutes if wholly or partially cooked.
Add vegetables together about 2 minutes.
Remove shrimp and vegetables; put in a covered container with the eggs to keep warm.
Heat remaining 4 tablespoons oil in wok or skillet; add the cooked rice.
Fry over high heat until coated with oil.
Return vegetables and eggs to wok.
Stir; add soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello well.
Add pineapple, mandarin oranges and cottage cheese.
Mix well and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.

title: coconut bars
directions: Cream together margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Pat into a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and make into a ball.
Chop 1/2 package beef and roll ball in it.
Serve with Ritz crackers or your choice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar.
Let set overnight or at least 6 hours.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops on bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with onion and sprinkle with salt.
Pour uncooked rice over onions and chops.
Add tomato soup thinned with water.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: golden cheddar broccoli
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually, mixing until smooth.
Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix in 1/4 cup cornflake crumbs and corn.
Arrange broccoli in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining 1/2 cup crumbs with 2 tablespoons margarine (melted) and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls on greased tin.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: In
large
