bowl beat eggs until foamy.	Add sugar, corn syrup, butter,
salt
and
vanilla;
blend.
Stir in peanuts. Pour into pie
shell; bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes until set.
Serve warm
or cold.
Try garnishing with whipped cream or ice cream, topped with peanuts.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla with electric mixer about 5 minutes.
Line pans with midget baking cup papers.
Put 1 heaping teaspoonful of crushed wafers into bottom of each cup. Press slightly; fill 3/4 full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.

title: best hot chocolate
directions: Mix together.
Pack in decorative jars as gifts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add pineapple, half of pecans to cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll cheese ball in rest of pecans.
Wrap for storage.
I use a few more pecans.
You may want to chill cheese ball before rolling in the pecans.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough on greased pizza pan or cookie sheet and bake as directed.

title: low-fat oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Beat egg, brown sugar and oil with electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in yogurt and vanilla.
Add oats, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in raisins.

title: squash or eggplant casserole
directions: Cook squash or eggplant. Add mushroom soup, eggs, onion and cheese. Add half of crumbs. Pour in casserole and top with oleo. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: enchiladas de jocoqui
directions: Wash chiles; remove seeds and cut each in 1/3's lengthwise. Heat 1/4 oil in skillet.
Fry each tortilla in oil to soften. Drain on paper towels.
On each tortilla, place 1/4 cup cheese and 2 chile strips.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and add 2 tablespoons Salsa Rapida de Chile.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with layer of salsa.
Roll each tortilla and place seam side down in the salsa.
Mix white sauce and sour cream; pour all over, then drizzle with a cup of the salsa.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat lime juice and milk well and add green food coloring. Beat Cool Whip and blend, then put into a chocolate pie crust. Crush Oreo cookies and sprinkle on top for decorations.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Stir tomato, onions, green pepper, jalapeno pepper, lime juice, salt, pepper, oil and cilantro together.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving at room temperature.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Yield:
1 cup (2 servings).

title: oklahoma chili
directions: Brown meat; saute onion and garlic.
Add to meat mixture. Stir in chili powder, oregano, cumin and crushed red pepper; mix well.
Add broth, tomatoes (juice and all), tomato paste, salt and sugar.
Stir well, breaking up tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: steak sauce from the middle ages
directions: Soak roll in stock, then puree in blender.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and almonds; mix together until well blended.
Refrigerate, covered, or the fridge will "remember" the sauce for days.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain green beans.
In a large saucepan, combine butter, flour, salt, pepper, sugar, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Stir and cook over low heat until ingredients are well combined and cheese melted.
Add beans, mixing well. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine cornflakes with 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle over bean mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese and tomato quiche
directions: Place a layer of tomatoes over Cheddar cheese in pie shell. Blend eggs, flour, sour cream, half and half, soy sauce and salt. Pour over tomatoes.
Put onion and pepper on top.
Add water chestnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sauce for vegetables
directions: Put butter in saucepan to melt.
Stir in flour and let cook until it begins to foam.
Then stir in milk and cook until it thickens.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Mix well. Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: tortilla dippers
directions: Combine cream cheese and chilies.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Slice into 1-inch pieces and put toothpick into each one.
Dip in salsa to eat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and banana pulp.
Add sifted dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and add nuts. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cucumber salad with yogurt
directions: In a bowl, layer cucumbers with salt.
Cover with saucer and weight with heavy object (such as large fruit can).
Let stand at room temperature 1 to 2 hours or until cucumber juices are drawn out.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Chill.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition, until well blended.
Fold in raspberries, reserving a few for garnish.
Place crust on baking sheet.
Fill with raspberry mixture and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool completely and chill.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Line pie pan with vanilla wafers (sides, too).
Let cream cheese soften.
Mix whipped cream and sugar.
Cut cream cheese in chunks and add gradually until smooth.
Pour cream mixture into wafer lined pan.
Add cherry pie filling on top.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased iron skillet and bake at 350° until done.

title: fruit dip ii
directions: Mix together.
Blend well; add any color to go with your fruit tray.
Apples, bananas and strawberries are the best.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add salsa, corn, chili powder and Miracle Whip.
Layer 1/2 meat mixture in baking dish, top with 1 cup tortilla chips and 1/2 cheese. Repeat remainder of meat mixture, chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, bread crumbs and butter. Coat chicken breasts with mustard, then dip into crumb mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until chicken is done. Serves 6.

title: dolphin inn new orleans style french toast
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients 100 strokes with wire whisk.
Slice bread about 3/4-inches thick.
Dip individually in mix and drain excess.
Brown on both sides on griddle coated with Pam or other no stick cooking spray.
Place on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beer beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook 35 to 45 minutes in saucepan, or you can cook it in a crock-pot.
Put it on early in the morning and when you get home in the evening, you won't be able to wait to eat.
Serve with French bread and a salad.

title: vermicelli with fresh herbs
directions: Mix oil, pinenuts, parsley, capers, rosemary, sage and basil. Stir in tomatoes. Cook vermicelli as directed on package; drain. Mix vermicelli and herb mixture. Serve with pepper.

title: sarah's vegetable antipasto
directions: Drain beans; place in glass or plastic jar.
Pour salad dressing over beans; cover.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
Prepare deviled eggs; chill.

title: special chicken and rice
directions: Combine salt, paprika, garlic powder and pepper.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings.
Brown chicken in ovenproof skillet. Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onions, green pepper and rice. Stir in broth and cumin.
Return chicken to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: ham and egg combo
directions: Blend 1/2 cup Miracle Whip salad dressing, 1/4 cup flour and dash of pepper.
Gradually add 2 cups milk.
Stir until thickened. Add 1/2 cup sharp Cheddar, Velveeta or American cheese (cubed) and 1/4 cup chopped onion.
Heat until cheese melts.
Then add 1 1/2 cups cubed, cooked ham and 4 hard-boiled eggs (sliced).
Serve on toasted English muffins or toast.
Serves 6 to 8.
You can increase quantities and make double batch and also use 2 kinds of cheese.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Combine crushed wafers, sugar and butter.
Form crust in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Pour blueberry filling over this and spread with Dream Whip.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top.
Let it be in refrigerator for 8 hours.

title: quick n' easy spinach lasagna
directions: Press all water from spinach.
Blend with Ricotta cheese. Spread 2 cups spaghetti sauce over bottom 11 x 16 x 2-inch lasagna pan.
Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagna noodles along the bottom of the pan to cover the sauce.
Spread Ricotta cheese mixture over noodles.
Arrange another layer of uncooked lasagna noodles over Ricotta cheese mixture.
Cover with half the Mozzarella cheese, all the grated Parmesan cheese and with remaining 4 cups of spaghetti sauce.
Top with remaining noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover pan tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pasta is cooked.
Remove foil and allow lasagna to cook an additional 15 minutes to brown cheese.
Serves 12.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 teaspoon curry powder and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice to make the sauce.
Partially cook frozen broccoli.
Partially cook chicken breasts.
Mix bread crumbs with 1 stick melted butter.
Place in casserole the broccoli, deboned chicken, sauce, layer of American or Cheddar cheese, bread crumbs and butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taffy
directions: Combine corn syrup, cream of tartar, water and sugar.
Cook to 265°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour onto greased platter. When cool enough to handle, pull until snowy white.
Cut with scissors.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together but vanilla and nuts.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Place a layer of graham crackers in bottom of dish.
Pour in half the filling.
Place another layer of crackers, then add rest of filling.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: texas nachos
directions: Spread a layer of chips on cookie tin or large oblong casserole.
Heat can of refried beans mixed with 1/3 can of water.
Spread on chips.
Top with shredded Monterey Jack cheese. Place sliced jalapenos over cheese (if you like things hot).
Put in 350° oven until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Mix turkey, mushrooms and cream cheese together and set aside. Separate
rolls
and
roll
out
with greased fingers. Fill rolls with turkey mixture.
Roll back up and seal rolls. Dip in	melted butter
and
roll	in
bread crumbs.
Place in 12-inch greased Dutch oven.
Cook for 25 minutes with 12 coals on top and 8 coals on the bottom.

title: gatlinburg pie
directions: Crush crackers; add 1/2 cup sugar and the nuts.
Mix together. Beat egg whites until stiff; add remaining 1/2 cup sugar to egg whites and vanilla.
Fold egg mixture into crackers.
Pour into a buttered pie pan and bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, spread whipped topping over pie and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Makes 2 deep-dish shells.
Boil potatoes; peel and mash.
Add sugar, flour, milk, eggs and vanilla; mix well, then add softened butter and mix.
Pour into 2 unbaked deep-dish pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Combine in saucepan until dates are mushy: dates, egg, sugar and butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Allow to cool and form into balls.
Roll in coconut while warm.

title: egg dish
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight in casserole dish in refrigerator.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Garnish, if desired, with whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Combine fish, mushrooms and sherry.
Melt Crisco. Stir in flour and salt.

Add milk and Worcestershire sauce. Stir constantly until thickened. Combine with fish and place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch rectangular dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve over toast or biscuits.
Top with hard-cooked egg quarters.
Any suitable fish may be substituted.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: The night before serving, mix cream cheese, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
This can be done quickly in a food processor. Chill overnight.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Put into 9-inch square pan.
Spread topping over dough.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 9 inch pie plate mix soup, vegetables and chicken.
In a bowl, mix milk, egg and Bisquick, pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter krispie bars
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and peanut butter together in a large saucepan.
Remove from fire and mix in cereal.
Stir until well blended.
Press immediately into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
A nice change from marshmallows!

title: moussaka(eggplant and ground beef casserole)
directions: Half unpared eggplants lengthwise; then slice crosswise 1/2 inch thick.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and let stand 15 minutes. Rinse with cold water; pat dry. Place in bottom of broiler pan and brush slices with 1/2 c. melted butter.
Broil 4 inches from heat 4 minutes each side.

title: squirrel gumbo and dumplings
directions: Make a roux by browning the flour and oil over medium heat until it is dark brown.
Put roux in deep gumbo pot.
Add the water.
Set on medium heat and stir until roux is blended with water.
Add onion, squirrels, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1/2 hour. Add the soup and stir until smooth.
Add strips of dumplings made from plain flour and water.
Cook until dumplings are done, on medium heat.
Serves 6.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Cover with boiling water.
Let set 10 minutes and drain off water.
Cover with water again.
Let boil.
Remove from fire.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain water. Add salt, vinegar and sugar.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: baked peach crunch
directions: Place the canned peaches and their syrup in 8-inch baking dish.
In separate pan, mix the melted margarine with cracker crumbs, oats, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir until mixture is crumbly. Spoon evenly over peaches.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is golden brown and bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with hands cream cheese, 2/3 of Cheddar cheese, chopped onion stems and meat.
Roll in a ball and coat with remaining Cheddar cheese and nuts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, and beat until it stands in peaks.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup of the onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Drop biscuits in bag to coat.
Place in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: speckled trout
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Chop cabbage into small pieces and add to sausage; let cook down.
Cook egg noodles; drain and mix all together.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked hominy and cheese
directions: In large bowl, beat egg; add hominy, cheese, milk, onion, bacon, oleo and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and top begins to brown.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley,
if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients for batter in usual manner.
Put brown sugar in deep bowl; add butter, nutmeg and boiling water and stir.
Pour sauce over batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until top is golden brown.
As this pudding bakes the batter rises to the top and the sauce stays on the bottom.

title: ann porter's mexican cornbread
directions: Saute meat and onion; drain well and dry off.
Do not brown onion, just cook until it is clear.
Sift together the cornmeal, salt and soda.
Add eggs, milk, corn and cheese.
Stir well with spoon.
Add meat, onion, peppers and 1/4 cup oil.
In a heavy skillet, add 2 tablespoons oil.
Heat on top of stove until smoky. Pour cornmeal mixture into hot skillet.
Cook at 400°for 30 minutes.
Turn
out onto a serving plate.

title: frypan cookies
directions: Combine dates, sugar, butter and eggs in frypan.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
In another bowl, shape into balls and coat in coconut.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover dish with foil and refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven the next day to 350° and cook, covered, for 40 minutes.
Remove the foil and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish or plastic bag.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 to 8 hours. Drain.
Dip chicken in combined crumbs and pecans; press to coat. Cook chicken in margarine in large skillet over medium heat 5 to 6 minutes on each side until tender.

title: basic marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use with beef, pork and chicken.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Add all ingredients in layers as listed.
Do not stir.
Flavor improves after salad stands several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line the bottom of the pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Top with second layer of cookies.
Then add rest of mixture.
Finish with third layer of crackers. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Put in roaster; put in 325° oven for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, drain off fat.
Then mix in bowl the other ingredients.
Mixture should be a little thick, not runny.
If mixture is too strong, you can add more water.
Pour some mixture in bottom of roaster; add ribs.
Pour remaining mixture over ribs; bake at 150° for 3 hours.
Baste from time to time.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; cook in salted water until tender. Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and may top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 30 balls.
Either bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes or fry.
Can use any kind of sauce as desired.

title: mouthwatering hamburgers
directions: In medium bowl combine beef, onion, garlic, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
In a small bowl combine cheese, mushrooms, bacon and mayonnaise; refrigerate.
Grill burgers over medium hot coals for 10 to 12 minutes, turning once.
During the last few minutes, spoon 1/4 cup of the cheese mixture onto each burger.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Combine in blender.
Process until smooth and thick.
Serve in tall glasses.
Can top with another scoop of ice cream.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Cover beets with mixture and simmer for 15 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break the crackers coarsely. Put into pastry lined pan. Combine the water, sugar and cream of tartar in a saucepan.
Boil gently 15 minutes; add lemon juice and peel. Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers. Dot with butter and sprinkle cinnamon. Cover with top crust. Trim fluted edges. Cut slits in top. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: pizza puffs
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Spray 13x9-inch non-stick pan.
Break up biscuits into 3 or 4 pieces and put in the bottom of pan.
Pour pizza sauce over biscuit pieces.
Cover with pepperoni and mushroom or other topping.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 20-25 minutes.

title: refrigerator raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix by hand all dry ingredients.
Add liquid and mix well. Store up to 6 weeks in tight container.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix spices with pumpkin pie mix.
Do not add milk.
Mix with hands for best results.
You be the judge as to how thick you want mixture.
Make it thick enough to cut with knife, but not fall apart.
Top with whipped cream around edges.
Cool.
We eat this Pumpkin Pie all year around.

title: rice krispie candy
directions: In large saucepan, combine honey and brown sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until well combined.
Add Rice Krispies, stirring until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: caesar salad de provence
directions: Preheat oven to 325. Cut loaf of French bread in half lengthwise (like for making garlic bread) then cut across loaf to make 1-1/2 inch strips.
Cut each strip to make 1-1/2 x 1-1/2 inch cubes.
Place the cubes onto a large cookie sheet or large square cake pan.
In blender or food processor, liquefy butter, olive oil, cheese, herbs, garlic and basil.
Pour liquid over bread cubes and VERY gently toss the bread to evenly distribute the liquid so the bread absorbs it evenly. Place in cookie sheet in oven for 10 minutes.
With spatula, toss the croutons to again distribute the liquid and evenly brown each cube.
When the edges of all croutons are browned, remove from oven and place in brown paper bag.

title: lobster newberg
directions: Make a sauce mixture of the first 8 ingredients.
In an iron pan, melt some butter.
Saute meat of a 4 pound lobster.
Add remaining ingredients to sauce.
Put in a buttered casserole and bake until brown on top in a 350° oven.

title: cherry dream dessert
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix until well blended; spread mixture on crust.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix and cook in microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir and add 1 tablespoon butter. May add 1 drop yellow food color. Cook and stir until thick. Will be thicker when cool.

title: chili with beef
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, onion and green pepper until beef is browned and the onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and their tomato juice and spices.
Heat to the boil, reduce heat and cover; simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans; heat thoroughly.
Makes four servings.
Garnish with grated Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: butter roll
directions: Roll biscuit dough into rectangle.
Cut butter into pieces and place on dough.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on dough.
Roll up dough and place in a loaf pan.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar in 1 cup milk; pour over roll.
Bake at 350° until roll is brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Put in a crock-pot and serve with corn chips.

title: apple butter
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Boil sweet cider until it is reduced one-half.
Add apples to cider while boiling.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, so as to prevent burning.
When it begins to thicken, add sugar and spices.
Cook until it remains in a smooth mass.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese and paprika, in a 11 x 13-inch pan.
Grate Cheddar cheese over it.
Sprinkle paprika over.
Bake until bubbly in a 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the oil and sugar; beat in eggs. Thoroughly stir together the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean in a 350° oven.

title: english toffee
directions: In 2 or 3 quart heavy sauce pan, melt butter over a low heat. Add the sugar and lecithin and stir constantly with a wooden spoon over
a medium high heat, until mixture comes to a boil. Add the corn syrup and continue to cook over a medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent burning in the bottom, until temperature reaches 295°.
Remove from heat.
To the cooked mixture, add salt and nuts and gently mix in.
Pour into a well buttered shallow pan.
Smooth out with a knife to a thickness of approximately 1/4 inch.
Before toffee sets and becomes firm, score into uniform rectangles about 1 inch by 2 inch size, with a knife.
When cool and firm break into rectangular pieces. Toffee pieces can be left uncoated or they can be dipped in chocolate.
Toffee should be stored in a air tight container or plastic bag to prevent softening.

title: lemon cake
directions: Add ingredients together in mixer.
Pour in lightly greased tube or Bundt pan.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate mint mousse
directions: Mix mints, eggs, sugar and chocolate chips in blender.
Scald milk; add to mix; mix until smooth.
Refrigerate 30 to 40 minutes. Whip cream.
Remove from refrigerator.
Fold cream into mousse. Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian fried peppers with onions
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy skillet; saute peppers and onions until onions are pale gold, about 5 minutes.
Stir; cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, shaking the pan from time to time.
Uncover; cook 2 minutes more.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Serves 4.

title: easy candied carrots
directions: In saucepan combine ingredients and simmer for a half hour. Serve hot.

title: cream cheese zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and powder and cream cheese until frothy.
Add grated zucchini and mix well.
Add flour and beat 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts; turn into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Frost as desired or dust with powdered sugar.

title: my irish indian grandmother's spaghetti sauce
directions: In frypan, brown hamburg and sausage (take out of casing and cut up).
Add onion and pepper and cook until soft; drain.
Put tomatoes in a saucepan (mashed).
Add sugar and Italian flakes to taste.
Add hamburger and sausage mixture to this.
Add tomato paste and sauce, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and chill, covered.
Serve with cold or fried seafood.

title: aunt sherry's ham sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well in blender or food processor on low speed until well blended.
Store in the refrigerator.
Will keep for several months.
Serve with hot or cold ham or as a spread for ham sandwiches.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Return to oven until golden brown (about 15 minutes).

title: fat apples
directions: Pan-fry fat back.
Drain oil, except for approximately 1 teaspoon.
Add sliced or chopped apples.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and other seasonings to taste.
Cover and simmer until apples are soft by fork-touch.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press in bottom of oblong pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Melt cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Spread pie filling on top. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in bowl. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix potatoes and 1/3 cup milk. Add all at once to flour. Stir with fork just until evenly moistened.

Gather in a ball; pat out on well-floured surface to 3/4-inch thick. Dip biscuit cutter in flour; cut out. Place 1 1/2-inches apart on lightly sprayed baking sheet. Brush with 1 tablespoon milk. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden.

title: most excellent party cheese dip
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil with fresh chopped jalapenos.
Stir in flour with fork.
Add evaporated milk to thicken to consistency of thick soup.
Add chopped tomatoes and allow mixture to thicken.
Add Velveeta and lime juice.
Add scallions, if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: In bowl, combine egg, a dash of garlic salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Pound out breasts and cut off any fat; dip in egg mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: germantown pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add some liquid to flour and mix.
Add to rest of liquid.
Do same for eggs.
Add vanilla. Divide equally into 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: raisin cookie bars
directions: Cook over low heat until thick.

title: russian fluff
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain grease.
Cook rice only partially.
Mix soups together in large mixing bowl.
Mix in 1/2 cup water.
Pour hamburger and rice into soup mixture.
Add water to make firm, but not dry.
Mix in peas. Put into casserole dish and break bread on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: baked pork chops with potatoes
directions: Lightly
brown pork chops.
Mix soup, sour cream, water and parsley together, forming a sauce.
Into a greased casserole, alternate
a
layer
of
sauce, 1 of potatoes, salt and pepper to taste,
with
a
layer of sauce on top.
Place pork chops over potato mixture.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: okinega class favorite green beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings and add onion and brown lightly.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and dry mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir liquid into skillet and cook, stirring, until mixture starts to boil.
Blend in brown sugar and vinegar.
Add green beans and heat.

title: horseradish carrots
directions: Clean and cut carrots into lengthwise strips.
Cook carrots and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon melted oleo and a dash of paprika.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: simply apple
directions: Grease pie plate.
Fill 2/3 full of peeled apples.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon on top with nuts.
In small bowl, combine margarine, 3/4 cup of sugar, flour, egg, baking powder and salt.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: louisiana yam ring
directions: Mash hot yams in large bowl with milk, salt and pepper. Spread some of the margarine (about 5 tablespoons) over bottom and sides of 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Spread sugar over the margarine covered bottom and sides, pressing lightly.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom.
Blend remaining margarine with yams.
Spoon mashed yams into mold, spreading evenly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Fill center with creamed ham or chicken if desired.

title: cheese tortellini soup
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil in Dutch oven over medium-high flame.
Stir in vegetables and tortellini.
Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, over low flame for 7 minutes or until tortellini is tender.
Stir in parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon, mix other ingredients in and chill a few minutes in refrigerator.
Shape in rolls and roll them in pecans and parsley flakes.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice and eat on crackers.

title: tuna muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into tuna mixture.
Coat six muffin pans with oil or paper cups.
Fill with tuna mixture, mounding tops.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Run knife around to loosen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add strawberry gelatin. Put as many strawberries as you like in crust and pour mixture over berries in pie.
Top with whipped cream.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters.
Take a small amount of dough at a time and keep the other refrigerated.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.

title: goof ball candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl (except chocolate morsels) and form into balls.
Chill for 4 hours.
Melt chocolate morsels at 350° until melted.
Dip balls into melted chocolate.
Chill until firm.

title: biloxi barbecued shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, seasoning as desired.
Saute over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a heavy skillet, or bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes in a covered roasting pan. Yields 20 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 9x13 pan.
When you take it out of the oven, poke holes all over with a fork.
Mix the can of condensed milk and cream of coconut.
Pour this mixture over the cake while it is still warm.
Let the cake cool and spread the Cool Whip over it.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: ethan's veggie flower
directions: Wash celery stalk, trim ends and cut in half. Peel and slice the cucumber and carrots. Arrange one cucumber in center followed by 8 carrot rounds around it, Fill celery stalks with filling and place under the flower. Add spinach on each side for leaf effect.

title: 6 weeks slaw
directions: Pour this over the ingredients; do not stir.
Put in refrigerator and stir the next day.

title: snicker bar dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with one roll sugar cookies.
Cut Snicker bars into small pieces and line into next layer.
Cover with remaining sugar cookies and bake for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salmon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll balls in parsley flakes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until real crisp.
Take up.
Saute onion in the bacon grease.
Peel potatoes and cube.
Boil the potatoes in water and salt and pepper to taste until about done.
Put all of this together with creamed corn.
Add sweet milk and let simmer about 20 minutes.

title: caribbean cranberry salad
directions: Mix the jello with the boiling water. Add the cranberry sauce and stir until dissolved. Add the pineapple and water.
Chill.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp; rinse and soak in ice water.
Drain and mash with fork.
Add mayo to make spreading consistency.
Add lemon juice, onion salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: cool whip pudding
directions: Mix all except wafers together.
Layer the wafers.
Pour half of the mixture on wafers, then another layer of wafers.
Add the rest of the mixture.
Makes 2 layers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and add all together.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and brown top.

title: cranberry cherry pie
directions: Use favorite pie crust recipe or bought crust.
Combine cranberries, sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Add pie filling. Pour into crust and bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cover edge of crust with foil to prevent excessive browning.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put tomato paste and water in pot.
Stir in molasses, salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, onion, garlic and hot pepper.
Add meat and mix well.
Cook on low heat for 10 hours.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese (optional).

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, butter and Pet milk over hot water.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 cake mixture into long baking pan.
Bake for 14 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour melted caramel mixture over cake.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake 20 minutes.
Top with German chocolate icing, if desired.

title: spoon rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add butter, egg and sugar; mix well.
Stir in flour until thoroughly combined (batter will be soft).
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
The baked rolls can be kept in freezer bags in freezer. Thaw and reheat as needed.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Brown in oil the pot roast.
Pour off excess oil.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Strain liquid and measure; if needed, add water to make 4 cups.
Return to stove and add gingersnap crumbs to liquid.
Stir until thickened and cookie crumbs dissolve.
Pour over sliced meat.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: With sharp knife, cut chicken lengthwise into 1/2-inch wide slices; set aside.
In large bowl, combine oil, chili powder, cumin, oregano, garlic powder, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Mix well. Toss chicken in oil mixture until evenly coated.
Cover.
Marinate at room temperature several hours or refrigerate overnight.
Over high heat, prepare skillet.
Toss red and green pepper strips and onion with chicken mix.
Place in skillet.
Stir.
Cook until chicken is browned.
Remove pan from heat.
If desired, serve with warm flour tortillas, shredded lettuce, chopped green onions, cheese, salsa or sour cream.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour half into each pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: orange mints
directions: Combine half the sifted confectioners sugar, butter and corn syrup in large saucepan.
Cook mixture, stirring constantly until it comes to a full, rolling boil.
Stir in remaining confectioners sugar, vanilla, orange flavoring and food coloring.
Remove from heat and stir until mixture is cool enough to handle.
Pour onto waxed paper and knead until mixture is smooth.
Press into molds and let set until they'll hold the shape (3 to 5 minutes).
Pop out of molds onto waxed paper until firm enough to store.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 50 candies.

title: apricot swizzle
directions: Combine water, nectar, lemonade concentrate, sugar and tea powder; stir until sugar and tea dissolve.
Pour over ice in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in ginger ale; stir gently to mix.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a greased 2 x 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: winning cake recipe
directions: Beat well the margarine, cream cheese and vanilla.
Add sifted powdered sugar; mix well.
Add about half the pecans.
Frost and fill cake.
Sprinkle remaining pecans on top of cake.

title: easy micro lasagne
directions: Crumble sausage into 2-quart casserole.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes, breaking up and stirring after 4 minutes, until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cover tightly and microwave 3 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until hot.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, basil and egg.
Spread 1 1/3 cups of the sauce mixture evenly in rectangular dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2 or 13 x 9 x 2 inches.
Overlap 4 uncooked lasagne noodles on sauce.
Spread 1 cup of the cheese mixture evenly over noodles; sprinkle with 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers with sauce mixture, noodles and cheese mixture.
Top with remaining sauce mixture. Cover tightly and microwave on High 10 minutes; rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave on Medium (50%) 22 to 28 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: syrian flatbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead dough until smooth.
Divide into 12 balls.
Knead and roll flat with rolling pin (or press flat with hands).
Shake off excess flour.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 1/2 can of pineapple.
Bake and let cool completely.
Mix rest of pineapple, Cool Whip, cream cheese and vanilla pudding for icing.
Spread on cake evenly.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and juice from oranges.
Beat 3 minutes.
Fold in oranges.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef over noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 350° oven for 3 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mama's corn bread
directions: Gently beat eggs; add all the items to this.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon and mozzarella burgers
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Mix together sauteed onion, meat, bacon, cheese, celery salt, pepper and egg. Shape into 6 patties.
Pan-fry in the same pan used to fry onion.

title: breakfast sausage casserole(low fat)
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon margarine on each toast and cut each slice into quarters or small squares.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer ingredients in the following order until used up:
bread, sausage, cheese on top.
Mix in a separate bowl the eggs and milk. Pour this egg mixture over the other ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and quarter artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle extra Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir together syrup, sugars, water and salt in a saucepan and slowly bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Add maple flavoring to taste.
Makes a little over a pint.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt, ginger, cinnamon and baking soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, molasses and liquid.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Add more flour, if needed. Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour and mix well.
Add butter, eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Stir until well-blended.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli a little bit first, not all the way done.
Put all ingredients in a baking dish and sprinkle with cheese; bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 90 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions; cool slightly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk or water until light and fluffy.
Beat unbeaten egg whites one at a time into mixture.
Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with salt and baking powder.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with remaining liquid to cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Melt chocolate and combine with soda.
Divide batter into 2 equal parts.
Add chocolate mixture to one part.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into a greased and floured cake pan, alternating the white and chocolate batter until all is used.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: "miley's no-miss collards"
directions: Let ham hocks boil with cut up bell pepper and onion in enough water to cover meat.
Wash and cut up greens.
Put in pot of boiling meat.
Add salt, sugar and oil.
Let cook for 1 1/2 hours. Stir frequently until tender.
Serve hot.

title: cheddar pot pie crust
directions: Whisk flour, salt, baking powder and cayenne. Rub in cheese. Cut in butter. Knead in vinegar and water. Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper.

title: carrot cake
directions: This cake can be done in 2 or 3 layers depending on size of pans.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; set aside.
Cook noodles approximately 5 minutes; drain.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake until bubbly and slightly brown, approximately 20 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Can top with Cheddar cheese if desired.
Serves 4.

title: gazpacho(cold mexican soup)
directions: Put 2 cups of tomato juice and all other ingredients except diced tomato, chives and lemon wedges in the blender.
Blend until well mixed.
Slowly add the remaining 2 cups of tomato juice to the blender.
Pour the mixture into a large bowl and add the chopped tomato.
Garnish with the chopped chives and serve with the lemon wedges.
Makes 8 servings.

title: preacher's cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk in a pan and boil 3 minutes (no longer).
Add cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Beat quickly while hot and drop on baking sheets.
Wait 5 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Set aside.
Mix all ingredients well with macaroni.
Chill before serving, about 1 hour.

title: lemon coconut meringue pie
directions: Mix pie filling with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and egg yolks.
Stir in remaining water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar. Beat until stiff. Fold in coconut.
Spread over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 4 hours.

title: better-than-potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, celery, onion, mustard and salt.
Stir into chilled rice.
Cover and chill.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Wash rice. Melt margarine in casserole dish. Add rice and soups.
Cover dish and bake at 350°.
After 20 minutes, stir and bake another 20 minutes.

title: ham patties
directions: Combine meats, bread crumbs, eggs, salt and milk into patties using 1/2 cup per patty.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over patties.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: fish chowder
directions: Combine vegetables and salt; add water to cover and boil 10 minutes.

title: whip cream pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour; mix well. Add whipping cream and vanilla flavoring.
Do not preheat oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: zucchini and corn(calabacitas con maiz)
directions: Wash zucchini thoroughly and dice.
Do not peel.
Heat bacon drippings or oil in large skillet.
Simmer zucchini, corn and onion in covered skillet over low heat 15 to 20 minutes until tender and lightly browned.
Serve hot with tortillas.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pesto pasta
directions: In food processor blend oil, basil, walnuts and garlic.
Blend until basil is completely chopped.
Salt to taste.
Pour over hot pasta and toss.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, shortening and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate dough for several hours. Shape into 1-inch round balls and roll in white sugar.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: teriyaki beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except beef.
Slice the sirloin or top round in 1/8-inch slices.
Cut across the grain.
Mix together with the first mixture.
Cover and set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Cook in skillet for 3 minutes on medium heat. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: depression cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, raisins, hot water, vegetable oil, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Continue cooking at a low boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Meanwhile, sift flour with baking soda.
Blend dry ingredients with cooled raisin mixture.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts, if desired.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cake top springs back to the touch.
Makes 12 servings, each with 492 calories, 17 grams fat and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Then add shrimp, crabmeat or lobster.
Chill overnight for better taste!

title: zucchini silver dollars
directions: Put zucchini in large bowl.
Add eggs, scallions, mint, parsley and cheese.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add spices. Drop mixture by tablespoons into the very hot oil.
Fry until both sides are brown.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and honey.
Combine apples, celery, nuts and grapes.
Fold in the dressing and chill.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Combine and boil together several minutes.
Serve steaming hot.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mexican magic casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat in saucepan the soup, seasoning mix, beans, Ro-Tel and water.
After heated, mix with ground beef.
Line bottom of casserole dish with Doritos.
Spread sauce over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled peppers(makes 4 pints)
directions: Let stand 5 minutes,
then boil 5 minutes.
In each jar add 1/2 teaspoon
salt	and
1	teaspoon
oil.	Pour
vinegar solution over peppers
that	have been drained and packed into jars.
Hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add enough of flour to make stiff dough.
Roll very thin on a floured surface; let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Spread out and dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup or boiling salted water and cook 10 minutes.
Makes 3 cups uncooked noodles.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together.
Add crushed ice to chill.
Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: *To toast coconut, heat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut in thin layer on shallow baking pan.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until light golden brown.

title: orange angel dessert
directions: Pour 1/2 cup orange juice over each side of the cake on the outside, piercing with a fork so all juice will be absorbed.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, powdered sugar and rest of orange juice together.
Blend and spread less than 1/2 of it over the bottom layer.
Put top layer on and frost the whole cake.
Sprinkle with orange rind and refrigerate 24 hours before cutting.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour. Add sugar. Cut in butter, eggs and vanilla. Make a smooth dough. Chill. Roll out real thin and cut with cookie cutter. You will need to sprinkle flour on waxed paper to roll out and add flour as needed to keep dough from sticking. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Combine Kahlua with cream de cacao and divide among six mugs or heated wine glasses.
Top with cream and sprinkle with cocoa.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; stir occasionally until it forms a hard ball.
Beat two egg whites until fluffy.
Add the jello gradually and beat until mixture holds a stiff peak.
Pour syrup into egg whites, beating constantly, until it loses its glossy look.
Add nuts and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put in large cake pan.
Add 1 large package of Tater Tots on top.
Bake 400° for 35 minutes.

title: aunt louise's chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding per package instructions.
Stir in cake mix. Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake per cake mix instructions.
Cut into small squares to serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Layer broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Next, layer chicken (boneless).
Mix soup, curry, lemon juice and mayonnaise together; layer this over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs and dot butter over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef and pork in a bowl.
Soak the bread in the milk and shred.
Mix with the meat, onions and most of the catsup (reserve 2 tablespoons).
Break in the eggs and season.
Mix well together. Form into a loaf and place in a greased baking dish.
Spread the remaining catsup over the top to form a crust.
Place 6 slices of bacon over the top (optional).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: yummy apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and enjoy.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all together in large mixing bowl. Pour in greased and floured 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet with rim. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter.
Spread in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour on top of cake mixture, distributing evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and refrigerate.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges (juice too) until the oranges are in tiny pieces.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: patongco
directions: Mix all ingredients that comes in the Patangco mix with water and oil with mixer on medium speed.
Develop dough 15 minutes, then roll it up with a rolling pin to 4 cm.
Roll to twin sizes. Fry them and eat them.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Sliver dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Place raw chicken on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Remove lid last 30 minutes to brown chicken.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening in mixer bowl until light. Add sugar gradually, beating at medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in cream cheese.
Add flour alternately with eggs, beginning and ending with flour and mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Cream the margarine and sugar. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Roll the dough on a floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut the dough with a biscuit cutter. Place the biscuits on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes.

title: oven omelet(yields 6 servings)
directions: Blend together the eggs, sour cream and salt.
Stir in cheese. Add ham, bacon, mushrooms, etc.
Pour egg mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Tilt dish to distribute butter over top.
Dish has soft texture and is easy to prepare.

title: chili sauce
directions: Tie spices in a cheesecloth; add to other ingredients.
Cook slowly on low heat until thick like preserves.
Can cook on medium to high heat; keep eye on it.
Stir often.
Use wooden spoon for stirring.
Seal in hot jars.

title: pecan dreams cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in date size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on lightly greased sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crusts and cut bread in one-inch cubes.
Melt oleo and cheese in double
boiler until rarebit consistency; remove from heat and add egg
whites.
Working
quickly, dip cubes of bread into cheese mixture,
coating
well.
Place
cubes,
not touching, on a
greased
cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix, then gradually add powdered sugar until right texture.

title: two hour turkey
directions: Line baking pan with foil. Spray with Pam or grease with oil. Sprinkle salt and lemon pepper in cavity and under neck skin. Put onion under neck skin; fold wings under back and pull neck skin under wings. (Do not put salt on top; it won't brown evenly.) Put a handful of parsley stems and 1 teaspoon of rosemary in cavity. Tie legs together loosely. Put all ingredients (including giblets) around turkey, carrot, celery, 1 large onion, and 1 teaspoon rosemary. Heat the consomm and tomato juice and pour around turkey. Cover turkey with single foil. Do not let top foil touch turkey. Bake at 425° for 1 hour on lowest rack; remove and slit top of foil. Open foil and push to side. Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 400°. Do not baste.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit and cookies. Especially good with strawberries and grapes.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Put berries and juice in saucepan; turn on medium heat.
Add sugar and cornstarch; stir until thickens.
Before pouring into crust, put sliced butter pieces under top crust (before you put it on).
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: gruyere potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Lightly butter a 13x9-inch casserole.
Layer potatoes on bottom of casserole so they are barely overlapping.
Top with onion.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Put 2 more layers of potatoes, onion, seasoned salt and pepper, ending with potatoes.
Pour broth over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown and bubbling.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing into squares. Serves 12.

title: popovers
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and stir gradually into flour to make a smooth batter.
Beat thoroughly with eggbeater.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° for 20 minutes.
Delicious served with spaghetti, casseroles, etc.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with chives, seasoned salt and drained pineapple.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: tuna broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender; drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add broccoli, tuna and rice to soup and sour cream mixture.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with mixture of melted butter/bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Serve hot with Ritz crackers.

title: graham cracker cookie
directions: Cook the brown sugar with the butter and bring to a boil. Cook 4 minutes.

title: microwave twice-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and rinse well.
Pierce at intervals with fork. Arrange in circle, 1-inch apart, on paper towels in microwave oven. Cook at 100% power for 16 minutes, turning potatoes over after 8 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Remove 1/4-inch horizontal slice form top of each potato.
Using teaspoon, carefully remove pulp, placing in mixing bowl. Set shells aside.
Add butter, sour cream, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup grated cheese, chives and bacon bits (to taste) to pulp.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Divide mixture evenly and spoon into shells.
Sprinkle tops with remaining cheese.
Place in circle on microproof dish. Cook at 100% power for 4 minutes.

title: french pineapple delight
directions: Add 1/2 cup melted butter to crushed vanilla wafers. Spread mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press firmly to form crust. Mix 1/2 cup melted butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Small amount of pineapple juice may be added to make mixture creamier for spreading. Spread mixture over vanilla wafer crust. Top creamed mixture with pineapple. Spread thawed
Cool Whip topping over pineapple. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: butter cream icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Ice cake immediately.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix.
Add enough mayonnaise or salad dressing to toss together.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Chill thoroughly and serve on lettuce leaf with tomato wedges, boiled egg or olives. Serves 6.

title: beef enchilada pie
directions: While meat is browning, cut tortillas into strips.
Mix all other ingredients.
When meat is brown, add to other mixture.
In baking dish, place layer of tortillas and layer of mixture. Repeat process.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of dish with vanilla wafers, then layer of sliced bananas.
Repeat until desired thickness.

title: avgolemono soup(greek rice soup)
directions: Cook rice in broth with butter until tender.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks.
Add egg yolks and lemon juice.
Slowly combine mixture with broth and rice so eggs do not cook.
Serve hot with pepper and Italian bread chunks.
Enjoy!

title: pork chops german style
directions: Cover bottom of a casserole dish with bacon.
Top the bacon with an inch layer of sauerkraut.
Lay pork chops close together on top of the kraut and top chops with a layer of onion rings. Next, add a layer of potatoes.
Cover with a can of solid packed tomatoes.
Season with salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Cover and bake at 350° until done, approximately 2 hours.
For a large crowd, repeat layers.

title: broccoli roll-ups
directions: Pre-cook spears for 5 minutes.
Place slice of ham and slice of cheese on a flat surface.
Place a broccoli spear in center of each and roll and secure with toothpicks.
Place in a buttered casserole dish and top with your favorite cheese sauce.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: fruit punch for kids
directions: Combine concentrates, drink mix and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in water gradually.
Add ginger ale and ice just before serving, stirring gently.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Put on greased baking sheet in 2-inch balls and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar
directions: Pour ingredients into a small mixing bowl and mix well. Use as brown sugar in your favorite baked recipes where brown sugar is required. Makes 1/4 c., enough to replace 1 c. of standard brown sugar.

title: orange-mincemeat pie
directions: Crumble mincemeat into a saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook, stirring until lumps are broken and mixture comes to a boil. Boil vigorously for 1 minute.
Cool.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until spoonful of mixture mounds slightly.
Fold in mincemeat and walnuts, then whipped cream (Dream Whip).
Pour into baked shell.
Chill until firm.
We like this because the orange gelatin takes some of the sharp mincemeat flavor away.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash; add sugar.
In casserole dish, layer marshmallows, coconut and potatoes in that order. Melt oleo; remove from heat and add brown sugar and pecans.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 400° oven until bubbly.

title: italiano meat pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
In large skillet, brown beef.
Drain well.
Add green pepper and cook 2 minutes. Stir tomato sauce, mushrooms, water, oregano, basil and garlic powder.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle half the Parmesan cheese over bottom of pie crust.
Spread half the beef mixture over Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Layer rest of beef and Parmesan cheese.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Return to oven 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party pizzas
directions: Mix sausage, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Spread thinly on each slice and top with grated cheese.
Spray pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first nine ingredients.
Put into well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese and crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° or 350° until heated through and the top is boiling.
Set aside for a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Layer tomatoes, rice, broth and chicken.
Sink chicken in broth.
Add seasoning.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: celery soup(sellerisuppe)
directions: Wash celery roots and pare them.
Cut each into 4 parts.
Cover with salted boiling water; cook until tender.
Drain.
Reserve 2 cups water.
Cut half of celery in small pieces and save for soup tureen.
Rub other half through sieve.
Melt butter in soup pot. Stir in flour.
Add liquid, little by little and let come to boil. Mix egg yolk with a little water and stir into soup.
Add the peas, pepper, salt and sherry.
Stir and pour over the celery into the soup tureen.
Add parsley.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crumble cookies.
Melt butter and pour over half of Oreos.

title: raisin spice loaf
directions: Combine in saucepan, brown sugar, 1 1/4 cups water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool. Then add a mixture of baking soda, salt and 2 teaspoons of water.

title: wonderful yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt until warm.
Stir until shortening melts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Prepare Cream Sauce. Stir in cheese, heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the cheese is melted.

title: microwave stuffed manicotti
directions: Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes the beef, onion and garlic.
Stir 1 time.
Drain and set aside.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes the spinach.
Drain well.
Combine beef, spinach, dill, parsley, eggs and cheeses.
Stuff shells.
Spread on bottom of 12 x 8-inch casserole with 1 cup sauce.
Arrange stuffed noodles in dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour remaining sauce. Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put 2 tablespoons filling and a little grated cheese in each tortilla.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining sauce, sour cream and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.
If desired, add jalapeno peppers, cooked chicken, turkey, crab meat or shrimp.

title: valeskas' lemon bread
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together. Add the eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, milk and grated lemon rind.
Bake in loaf pan or tube cake pan at 325° for 50 or 60 minutes.
Top with the glaze.

title: potatoes and spam casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in pan.
Add onions and Spam.
Combine soup, milk, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and meat.
Bake until potatoes are tender or about 45 minutes.
Place cheese on top.
Heat until melted.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine whipped topping, pudding mix, orange, crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Cover.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, layer salad with bananas and strawberries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dressing for cole slaw or potato salad
directions: Blend Miracle Whip and sugar.
Add vinegar and stir well. Stir in enough milk to desired consistency.

title: pasta with primavera sauce
directions: In a large skillet, saute broccoli, zucchini, red pepper and snow peas in butter until tender-crisp.
Add half and half and pepper; cook briefly until slightly reduced.
Serve over linguini; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Put sugar, egg whites, vanilla and other ingredients in top of double boiler.
Beat until stiff.
Makes enough frosting for 2 layer cakes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; reserving liquid.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Bring liquid, both puddings and Tang to a boil over medium heat; stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and shiny; let cool.
Add drained fruit and sliced bananas; refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: no-fail microwave fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook in microwave, uncovered, for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and stir until thick.
Add flour.
Add chocolate mixture, salt and vanilla.
Nuts or coconut may be added.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Use an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: rice balls
directions: Add rice to salted water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer until rice is mushy.
Remove from heat, add oleo and cinnamon.
Cool.
Fry meat in 1/4 cup oil until loses redness.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 1 hour; stir occasionally.
Remove from heat, add parsley, cheese, salt and pepper.
Set aside to cool. Roll into firm balls, using 1 tablespoon meat mixture.
Chill and dip into beaten egg.
Roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Fry in hot deep oil until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco seasoning and spread on cookie sheet. Sprinkle onions, lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and olives.
Scoop up with corn chips and dig in!

title: caramel apple bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix brown sugar, butter and shortening in large bowl. Stir in the 1 3/4 cups flour, the oats, salt and baking soda. Reserve 2 cups of this mixture. Press remaining mixture into ungreased 13x9 in. pan. Toss apples and the 3 Tbsp. flour. Spread into pan. Heat caramels over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted. Pour evenly over apples. Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture. Press lightly. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Cut into bars while still warm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add extracts and vanilla; beat well. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
I start testing it about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Then add sugar, milk and cocoa.
Cook over medium heat until it boil, stirring often.
Boil for 1 minute, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Immediately drop by spoon onto waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add oil and eggs, one at a time.
Add 7-Up and blend until mixed well.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cake will be done when it springs back up to touch.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: hall's fundo!
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with a spoon.
Stir warm water and Borax until Borax is dissolved.
Pour the first mixture into second mixture.
Don't mix or stir.
Watch the change.
Pour out excess water and knead mixture a few times.
Store in an airtight container; do not refrigerate.
Not edible.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together; drain.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic salt; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and basil; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, eggs, salt and pepper.
Alternate layers of lasagna, cheese mixture, slices of cheese and meat mixture, repeating until all are used, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Put rice, salt and water in bowl.
Power level High for 4 minutes. Stir after 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and drain rice.
Add Cheez Whiz to warm rice.
Stir until melted.
Place unopened package of broccoli on end in microwave oven.
Microwave on High 4 minutes, turning over after 2 minutes; drain.
Add broccoli to rice and cheese mixture and stir in cream of chicken soup.
Put in casserole dish, microwave 3 minutes on High.
Remove and stir.
Microwave 3 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: creamy candy pralines
directions: Combine sugar and soda in a 3 1/2-quart saucepan; mix well. Stir in cream; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cook and stir to soft ball stage (234°). Remove from heat; add butter.
Stir in pecans; beat until thick, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over the mix.
Spread chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, covering loosely with foil to keep from browning too soon for the first half of baking time.
Cut into squares.
Serve.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in 2 tablespoons corn oil.
Place chicken in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with cheese, then return to oven just long enough to melt the cheese.
Serve over rice or noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter together.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts together.
Add to other mixture; mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and flour and spread in buttered pan (6 x 10-inches).
Now combine brown sugar, rolled oats, flour, margarine, shortening and salt.
Mix well; sprinkle over mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: meaty meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs and eggs by hand.
Pour oil into frying pan and heat on medium heat.
Roll meat mixture into 2-inch meatballs.
Place in hot oil.
Fry for about 20 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Open crescent dinner rolls and lay in pan. Cook as directed. When done, set aside. In a bowl to the side, mix Hidden Valley, mayonnaise, yogurt and cream cheese together. When mixed, spread over crescent rolls and top with your vegetable medley. Chill for 2 hours in the refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix milk and baking soda together.
Blend Crisco and sugar; add milk, flour and salt.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
An old recipe and very good.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix juice, ginger ale and vodka.
Freeze.
Put slush in glass; pour Squirt over slush when serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter; press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 1 hour.
Spread softened ice cream over crust.
Cover and freeze about 1 hour.
Pour hot fudge sauce over ice cream, cover and refreeze until firm.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Return to freezer.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: honey hot chocolate
directions: Heat, but do not boil.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: *Sliced in the package is better.

title: hot cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Spread 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on each of 8 bread slices.
Top with remaining bread slices and spread remaining cheese mixture on top of the sandwiches; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 8.
Freeze unbaked portion in freezer-proof wrap.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: In a 9 x 10-inch pan, put crisp cooked broccoli.
Then cut up cooked chicken breasts.
Mix the soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice, milk and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle all the shredded cheese on top.
Last put on the stuffing cubes.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour until bubbly.

title: smoked sausage appetizer
directions: Cut sausage links into 1/2-inch circles; put in frying pan and cover with water.
Heat to boiling.
Let simmer for 8 minutes. Drain; lower heat, remove lid and brown sausage on low heat for about 5 minutes.
While sausage is cooking, combine remaining ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat sauce to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
When sausage is done, add to sauce.
Serve in a chafing dish or in a baking dish on a hot tray. If you like it with more zing, add more horseradish and hot sauce to taste.

title: sunday breakfast casserole
directions: Brown onion and green pepper, then add meat and cheese.
Mix the eggs and milk.
Add hash browns, salt and pepper.
Mix all together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Serve with toast or muffins.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; mix 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 to 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Heat together sugar and butter until dissolves.
Add carrots and cook over medium heat.
Turn carrots until well glazed and tender.

title: ground beef okra stew
directions: Note:
If you wish, you can substitute cubed round steak for the ground beef.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mash asparagus and drain all liquid.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Serve at once.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine morsels, margarine and light corn syrup in medium size saucepan with Silverstone lining.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and sugar. Add Rice Krispies cereal, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Silverstone or if you don't have that, lightly butter the same size pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut with plastic utensil into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly; form into balls.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Let cool; peel and slice in thin round slices.
Do not dice potatoes.
Fry bacon, let cool and crumble.
Mix potatoes, onion, bacon, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil together.
Then add lettuce and stir gently.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cook the catfish in the water until it flakes easily. Remove fish to container to cool.

title: ribbon meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together bread and milk.
Mix in remaining ingredients except filling.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture in greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cover with Cheese Filling. Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: red wine vinegar pot or chuck roast
directions: Slowly brown meat in small amount of oil.
Sprinkle with salt (optional).
Combine all other ingredients; whip together and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours until tender.
Skim off excess fat from sauce and add flour and water to make gravy.
It is great in a crock-pot all day!

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in heavy aluminum foil.
Seal and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Place in pan of boiling water.
Boil for 1 hour.
Poke holes in bottom of foil; let drain on rack.
tags: Morton Tender Quick meat cure salt

title: banana bread
