directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour and soda. Then add hot water, bananas and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400° or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry rhubarb bake
directions: Mix all together; put into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together.
Place wings in mixture; marinate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drain marinade; save 1/2 cup.
Place wings in oven and cook 1 hour.
Baste after 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and mix together well. Press into ungreased 9 x 13 pan (mixture will be very thick). Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool. Turn oven to 350°. Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the crust. Return to the oven and bake for 35 minutes. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
This may be made ahead of time and refrigerated before baking.

title: mother jessie's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Heat grease in 9 x 9-inch pan until very hot.
While heating pan, mix in buttermilk and egg.
Pour in hot pan.
Bake until brown.

title: turkey melt
directions: Top each half of English muffin with turkey and tomato slices. Top with cheese slice.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cook pie shell according to instructions.
Mix sugar, cocoa and oleo.
Stir well.
Add eggs and beat with mixer for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add salt, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Mix sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in large kettle.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently, scraping the bottom and sides of pan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add butter and pecans.
Stir continually for five or more minutes.
After mixture reaches soft ball stage, remove from heat and let stand for 2 minutes.
Beat until thickened and creamy.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: pork chops with orange pilaf
directions: In large, heavy skillet, heat shortening or some of fat trimmed from the pork chops.
Add chops and brown slowly on both sides over low heat (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove chops to plate.
Add water to skillet with chopped onion, bouillon cubes, grated orange rind, celery salt, pepper, raw rice and broken egg noodles.
Heat to boiling, stirring until bouillon cubes dissolve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot pineapple juice. Add strawberries and juice to Jell-O. Put in refrigerator until almost set. Spread cream cheese mixture over top. Chill to set completely. Cut into squares.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions on box.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix in next 7 ingredients.
Crumble Cheez-Its crackers over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and peppers oriental
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a large skillet.
Add beef strips and cook until tender, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add soy sauce and cook 1 minute longer.
Pour into a large platter.
In same skillet, melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Saute peppers and onions for 2 to 4 minutes. Add beef strips, mixing well.
Garnish with fresh tomatoes, quartered.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.
Easy and good!

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown meat; cook bacon. Add onion. Drain hamburger; add together. Mix sugars, ketchup, smoke, mustard, salt and pepper. Do this in a separate bowl. Mix beans in meat mixture. Add other ingredients. Coat mix with sauce; add sausage. Put in pan and cover. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Combine peas, beans, green beans, corn, celery, onion, green pepper and pimento in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine vinegar, sugar, salad oil, salt, water and paprika and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss. Refrigerate for 24 hours in an airtight container, stirring occasionally.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Mix all, except butter.
Once mixed, add just enough melted butter to moisten (too much butter will make dressing soggy). Stuff turkey tightly. Bake as directed for regular turkey. Spoon out dressing whenever turkey is done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Drain shrimp.
Combine all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: friendship snack
directions: Have each child add a little bit of ingredients to the bowl. Explain to them how the never-ending circle of the pretzels continues without an end.
Explain that friends are supposed to be the same, together forever.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Make jello as instructed on box.
Stir Cool Whip and milk into vanilla pudding.
After jello is congealed, fold in crushed pineapple and marshmallows; set.
Pour vanilla pudding on top, then add coconut.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate butter fudge
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Mix sugar and dry gelatin in saucepan.
Add milk, syrup, chocolate and butter and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until soft ball stage (238°), ball flattens when taken from cold water.
Remove from heat.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Flavor with vanilla and cool 15 minutes. Beat until candy thickens.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, butter, salt and 1/4 cup milk in 1-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once or twice.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup of milk.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk until thick; add lemon pie filling, then 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust and put rest of Cool Whip on top of pies.

title: white pie
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups milk with about 1/4 cup sugar, then mix rest of ingredients together and add to hot milk.
Cook until thick; set aside to cool.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; fold into cooled mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle lightly with nuts (optional).

title: split pea soup
directions: In Dutch oven soak peas in cold water 1 hour.
Drain.
Add broth, celery, potatoes, onions, carrots, ham hocks, bay leaf and 1/2 teaspoon garlic.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf and ham hocks from soup.
Remove meat.
Blend soup in a blender to desired smoothness. Return meat and blended soup to pan.
Saute leeks and 1 tablespoon garlic in olive oil.
Add leek mixture, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: wafer ham cheese ball
directions: Chop ham in blender.
Reserve 1/2 to roll ball in.
Combine other ingredients.
Let chill before shaping.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease and flour Bundt or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
(Check at 50 minutes.)
Ice if desired.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Blend flour and water together.
Saut onion; blend onion, butter, flour and water.
Stir in cheese and salt until smooth. Then add beaten eggs.
Fold in well drained broccoli.
Grease dish and flour it.
Pour in broccoli mix.
Put crushed corn flakes on top and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in crisco, add buttermilk.
Knead dough till blended.
Should be doughy.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Roll dough to about 1/4 inch high.
Bake in a 450 degree oven for 10-12 minutes.

title: great "no crust" apple pie
directions: Slice apples and put in pie pan, mounded up.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.
Combine flour, sugar, margarine and beaten egg. Spread on apples.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put pan underneath!

title: oriental dip
directions: Mix all together. Serve with your choice of chips.

title: orange bread
directions: Cut oranges into eighths.
Boil 5 minutes in 1 cup water with salt or soda.
(This takes out the bitterness.)
Drain and rinse. Scrape off white membranes and discard them.
Cut peel into fine strips.
Bring sugar and 1/2 cup water to boil; drop in orange peel strips and cook for 5 to 10 minutes, until thickens and makes syrup.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook on top of stove at medium heat until all water has been absorbed and sugar is coated on peanuts.

Stir the peanuts frequently after the water has begun to thicken to a syrup so that the nuts will not burn. Pour peanuts onto ungreased pizza pan or shallow baking pan and spread fairly thin (the nuts will not stick together if you have a two-layer thickness).
Cook at 300° for approximately 30 minutes; stir at least once as nuts in the outer areas cook faster.
DO NOT COOK AT HIGHER TEMPERATURE AS SUGAR WILL MELT!

title: dill weed dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all together if using dill seed, keep refrigerated a couple hours longer.
Serve with all vegetables.

title: low-fat oven pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a bowl. Stir with a whisk.
Combine bread crumbs and paprika.
Dip chops in egg white mixture and bread crumbs.
Place on rack coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes each side.

title: jeweled fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch, with wax paper or aluminum foil (grease).
Mix all ingredients; spread in the pan.
Bake for about 1 3/4 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap; store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese needs to be very soft. Mix ingredients by hand thoroughly. Chill overnight then form ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Can be served on lettuce leaf.

title: navajo squaw bread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix into a smooth dough.
Pinch off small balls of dough and pat or slap over palms of your hands into a large circle that looks like a pancake.
Deep fry in hot, melted lard or oil.

title: 4-bean casserole
directions: Simmer 15 minutes bacon, onions, garlic salt, lemon juice, brown sugar and vinegar.
Add beans to the mixture in slow cooker on high until hot, then on simmer about 2 hours or longer or in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water and add flour and salt all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that won't separate.
Cool add eggs one at a time beating after each until smooth.
Drop by heaping tablespoon full 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown and puffy about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and split while warm. Cool on rack. Fill with pudding or cream filling.

title: crumb pie
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Mix flour and eggs together and add to mixture.
Boil a little longer.
Pour into unbaked crust.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken and vegetables in 13 x 9 pan (or larger).
Mix together soups and broth.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Mix well with other ingredients except butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add buttered bread crumbs and bake another 10 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: I mix a can of early June peas in with mine, sometimes green beans.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt 3/4 oleo in pan.
Add rice and stir.
Add soups, water and mushrooms; stir again.
Add salt and pepper.
Add chicken in remaining oleo and place on top of rice. Bake for 3 hours.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Melt butter, then add all the remaining ingredients.
Pour this into the pie shell.
Cook on 350° between 30 and 40 minutes. This will be firm, not hard.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Combine the 1 cup mashed squash and beaten egg; stir well. Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion; stir until blended.
Drop mixture by level tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in pan.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and paprika. Add onions, catsup and water.
Cover and bake 1 hour in moderate oven or until done.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook together until hot and bubbly, stirring frequently.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon. Remove from pan.
Saute onions in grease.
Add tomato paste, water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook uncovered slowly for about 10 minutes until mixture measures two cups. Then add it to rice.
Add the 1/2 cup of additional bacon grease. Cook for 1/2 hour on low with cover.
Add bacon, crumbled, and stir with fork.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together with fork.
Pour in pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese over top of baked pudding. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into bottom of a large bowl.
Cover with thin layer of celery chopped fine.
Put water chestnuts over celery. Sprinkle with peas.
Ice with 2 cups mayonnaise with 2 tablespoons sugar added.
Crumble bacon over top.
Slice eggs real thin over top.
Slice tomatoes thin and lay on eggs.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover with foil and chill.

title: creme puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boil.
Turn burner down to low, add flour and salt.
Mix until batter leaves sides of pan.
Let cool. When cool, add eggs one at a time.
Drop onto cookie sheet tablespoon at a time (make sure cookie sheet is greased).
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Drop down to 350° for 230 minutes.
When cool, cut tops and clean out insides.
Cover with confectioners sugar and fill with Cool Whip.

title: turkey salad
directions: Lightly mix the turkey, celery, chestnuts, onions, potatoes, parsley and dill.
Add yogurt and mix.
Add pepper to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: fettuccine with smoked salmon(from the four seasons restaurant, new york city)
directions: Prep time, 5 minutes; cook time, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. william a. falls delicate cake(heritage)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sifted flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add milk; fold in beaten egg whites.
Add flavoring. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 300° to 350°.

title: sea scallops with red peppers and tomatoes
directions: Cut the scallops crosswise (if they are more than 1 1/4-inches across).
Place scallops in a mixing bowl and add the milk, salt and pepper; set aside.
Place the flour in a flat dish and set it aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the red pepper, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until wilted.
Drain the scallops and dredge them in the flour.
Shake off the excess.

title: potato soup
directions: Simmer green onions, onion, butter and chicken broth until tender.
Fill with sliced potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Mash until you have small chunks.
Add half and half.
Serve with fried cornbread.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Fix vanilla pudding according to package instructions.
Cool and mix with Dream Whip.
Set aside.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except Swiss cheese and bread together. Slice bread (not quite all the way through).
Spread mixture on both sides of each slice of bread.
Place Swiss cheese between each slice.
Wrap each loaf in foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: one bowl apricot bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn out and cool on wire racks.
Store in cool place at least one day for best flavor.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix sugars, flour
or
clear
jell,
cinnamon and salt. Add to apples, stirring well.
Let stand overnight.
Cold pack in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon together. Sprinkle on top of fruit after it has been placed in baking dish. Bake in uncovered dish at 300° until fruit is tender, about 40 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; add cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add sour cream, garlic and butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Garnish with butter and paprika.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.
(Can be made ahead and baked following day.)

title: betty lou's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done (approximately 20 minutes).
While potatoes are boiling, prepare onion, green pepper and pimento. Place in a large mixing bowl.
Drain potatoes and add to bowl. Add mayonnaise and mustard; mix thoroughly.
May be served hot or cold.

title: new orleans bread pudding with lemon sauce and chantilly cream(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, beat the eggs on high speed until extremely frothy and bubbles are the size of pinheads, about 3 minutes (or with a metal whisk for about 6 minutes).
Add the sugar, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon and butter.
Beat on high until well blended.
Beat in milk, then stir in the raisins and pecans.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook, drain and rinse lasagna noodles.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Stir in soup, basil, milk, mushrooms and pimiento.
In a 9 X 13 pan, layer noodles, chicken, cheese, cottage cheese and sauce.
Repeat and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: walk-about
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add tomato juice, chili mix and beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Place chips in a large bowl.
Add chili mix and cheese.
Stir and serve while hot.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Combine water, broth, onion
and
broccoli.
Bring to a boil. Turn down heat and
simmer
for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and cream. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In 4 quart kettle, brown beef with salt and Italian seasoning. Add everything but soups and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add soups and water.
Simmer 30 minutes more.
Diced ham and slivered almonds can be added.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt until light.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with eggs and sour cream, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Mix lightly but surely. Pour into buttered muffin tins and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: chocolate chip surprise
directions: Spoon cookie dough into muffin cups. Bake for 8 minutes at 350 degrees. Put Reese cup in center of each cookie. Push down. Bake 2 more minutes.

title: nut rolls
directions: Mix dough as for pie crust, then add sour cream and egg yolks. Shape into small balls, the size of a walnut and store in the refrigerator overnight.
Roll each ball and spread with filling and roll up.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° about 30 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and water to which soda has been added.
Blend in salad dressing gradually.
Stir in flour all at one time, then add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes an 8 x 8-inch cake.

title: meme's orange cream cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake and drink mixes, eggs, 1 cup water and oil. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes. Pour in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Using a meat fork, poke holes in cake. Cool on wire rack for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool and then take chicken off bones.
Cook broccoli as per package directions.
Mix together soup, curry powder and 1 cup of grated cheese.
Line bottom of baking dish with cooked broccoli, lay the chicken pieces next, pour soup mixture over and sprinkle top with remaining cup of cheese.
Garnish with croutons.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese melts.

title: communion bread
directions: Sift the flour into a bowl.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles very coarse meal.
Add milk, 2 teaspoons at a time, mixing lightly until the dough looks and feels like pie crust dough.
Use more milk, if needed.
Form the dough into 2 balls. Wrap in waxed paper and chill for 1 hour or more.
Place 1 ball on a lightly floured board.
Roll until very thin and rectangular in shape.
With help of a spatula, place on bottom of a cookie sheet. Score dough in 3/4-inch squares.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Lift from pan immediately.
When cool, bread will break easily.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken or hen until tender. Debone chicken and place in casserole dish or pan and layer sliced eggs on top. Mix 2 or 3 cups of chicken broth with can of soup; pour over chicken. Mix milk, flour and melted butter. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour.

title: corkscrew macaroni toss salad
directions: Cook macaroni (do not use salt); drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Toss well and chill.

title: berry good topping
directions: In a blender, puree 1 cup of the berries with apple juice. In a small saucepan, combine apple juice concentrate and cornstarch; stir until smooth.
Add pureed berries.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Add vanilla and remaining raspberries.
Serve over yogurt, ice cream or pancakes.
Yields 8 servings (1 1/2 cups).

title: tomato corn chowder
directions: Brown lightly in large pot the ground beef and onion.
Drain and add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and green salad.

title: santa fe chili chicken
directions: Combine flour and chili powder. Coat chicken with this. In oil over medium heat, cook chicken until browned. Add gravy; cover and cook until chicken is done. Sprinkle with cheese. Serve with tortillas.

title: microwave pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place margarine into 8-inch round baking dish and microwave on High, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, or until melted. Tilt dish to coat sides.
Stir pineapple syrup and brown sugar into melted margarine in bottom of dish.
Arrange pineapple to cover bottom of dish.
Prepare butter cake as directed on package. Put into prepared dish, being careful not to dislodge pineapple. Microwave uncovered on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes during cooking.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Loosen edges.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add shrimp and seasonings, cooking until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add eggs, stirring until well mixed with other ingredients.
Add rice and cook until a golden color.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mash bananas and add to mixture gradually.
Add milk and flour, then add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, tomato, corn and mayonnaise.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: mary cooper's beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion in crock-pot, then add salt, liquid smoke, catsup, vinegar, sugar, canned beans and pepper. You can use any kind or amount of beans.
The meat mixture is enough for more and still be good.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend whipped topping and mayonnaise. Core and dice unpeeled apples into 1/2 inch squares. Fold into whipped topping mixture, add coconut and marshmallows. Add 1/2 of drained fruit cocktail, fold together lightly, pour into serving bowl.

title: gringo enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and spice as though you're making tacos.
Stuff the tortillas with the meat and cheese and roll item up like burritos.
Make them as big as you want.
Stack them side by side making a tight fit in your casserole dish.
Take the leftover meat and some cheese and spread in the gaps, along the sides and in all the groves.
Mix all your cans together in a bowl and add some cheese to the mix to make it thicker.
Spread that on top of your rolled tortillas ; then spread the cheese thickly on top of that. Heat it in the oven on about 300° to 325° until the cheese is good and melted.
Take the dish out and sprinkle with Parmesan on top. Serve with a salad and some sour cream on the side.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix together, add just enough sour cream for consistency.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix Karo and sugar in pan.
Heat until sugar is melted.
Add peanuts and salt (if not using salted peanuts).
Continue to cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture becomes amber in color. Turn off heat and stir in butter until melted.
Stir in baking soda.
When well stirred in, pour out mixture on a cookie sheet and let cool.
Mmmm! Good!

title: quick rice dressing
directions: Heat soup.
Add oleo and salt.
Add rice and stir.
Cover, remove from heat and allow to sit 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Bring to boiling stage, but do not boil.
Let cool.
Mash bananas in blender with pineapple juice. Mix banana mixture, orange juice, lemonade and sugar water mixture.
Pour in containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer for 6 hours before serving.
Serves about 50 people.

title: golden broiled fish steaks
directions: Place steaks on greased broiler pan.
Combine next 6 ingredients to make a butter sauce.

title: west virginia mustard greens
directions: Wash greens carefully with cold water to remove all the grit and sand.
Drain well.
Put water in 4-quart stock pot.
Add salt pork; bring to a brisk boil and then add greens (never put greens in cold water to start).
Salt to taste.
Add shortening; boil until tender, about 1 hour.
If frozen greens are used, cook according to package instructions.
Delicious with cornbread.

title: apple dessert pancakes
directions: Combine apples with sugar and cinnamon in saucepan.
Cover; cook until apples are tender.
Combine in small mixing bowl, eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Heat lightly greased skillet over medium-high heat.
Pour batter, 2 tablespoons at a time, into skillet.
Tilt pan to make a 6-inch round, thin pancake.
Brown about one minute; turn and brown on other side. Place about one tablespoonful apple mixture on each; roll up and place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, orange rind and orange juice.
Sprinkle over pancakes.
Broil 5 inches from heat, watching carefully, 2 to 5 minutes until golden brown and pancakes are hot.
Serve immediately with sour cream.
Makes 12 to 15 crepes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour into pan.
Cover with half the cheese.
Pour in the rest of the batter and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°).
Done when firm in center.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a small bowl mix pretzels, sugar and oleo.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Then mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Spread this over your pretzel crust. Then dissolve your jello in the hot water; stir in frozen berries and mix in pineapple.
When partially set, pour over the top of other two layers.
Refrigerate.

title: instant fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in salad bowl.

title: pork tenderloin in mustard cream sauce
directions: Split tenderloin in two lengthwise (not quite through); pound. Dip in flour.
Brown in oil and butter.
Transfer to shallow casserole.
In same pan, saute onions.
Take from heat and add garlic, vinegar and bay leaf.
Spoon over meat.
Cover all with sauce (recipe follows).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: edna's potato and sausage soup(salt-free recipe)
directions: Add sage, red pepper, pepper and onion powder to pork.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Fry next day.
Melt margarine.
Blend in flour.
Slowly add creamer.
Add Mrs. Dash.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add potatoes and cooked sausage.
This freezes well. It makes a large quantity of a very hearty soup.
I developed it for a person on dialysis who must control liquid intake as well as sodium and phosphorus.
If only sodium is the concern, milk may be used instead of nondairy creamer and potatoes do not need to be processed before cooking.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak the first 4 ingredients for 1 hour in the canning salt and water.
After 1 hour, drain.
Do not rinse. Set aside.
Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Add squash and onion and bring to a near boil.
Add pepper and pimento last to retain color.
Bring to full boil and remove from heat.
Pack in sterile hot jars and seal. Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute chopped onion in margarine. Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Mix next 3 ingredients for the dressing. Toss together.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; rinse in cold water and drain.
Combine spaghetti and chopped vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill overnight or several hours.

title: jello salad
directions: Pour fruit in pot and bring to a boil.
Add jello and mix well. Let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour fruit in Cool Whip mixture.
Mix and put in casserole dish.
Chill.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole in the following order: cream cheese, jalapenos, chili, cheese, onions and olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a small casserole dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: honey apple salad(low in fat, sugar and salt)
directions: In a large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
Add grapes, celery and dates.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, honey, sour cream and salt; mix well.
Pour over apple mixture and toss to coat.
Stir in the walnuts.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Then add flour and baking powder.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Spread peanut butter on while cake is still warm.
When cool, add chocolate icing.
Cut into squares.

title: diet cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low for several hours.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 2 to 3-inch patties.
Roll in additional cracker meal.
Fry in a little oil or bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, mushrooms and onion.
Dissolve bouillon in water. Add to beef.
Thicken broth with cornstarch.
Add sour cream to taste before serving.
Serve over noodles.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Slice the zucchini thin.
Mix all the ingredients well in a large bowl.
Bake in a pie plate at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit (drain canned fruit and cherries).
Sprinkle pudding mix over all and stir gently.
Makes a glaze over the fruit.
Bananas will not brown and can be made the night before.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Pour the orange juice and the pink lemonade into a pitcher. Add the pineapple and its juice and the strawberries (cut the large ones in half).
Peel the orange, separate into sections.
Cut each section into thirds and add to the fruit punch.
Fill pitcher with ice cubes and stir with wooden spoon until pitcher is frosty. Add fresh mint leaves before serving.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Top with 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salad oil; mix well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into 1/8-inch hot oil in large skillet. Flatten into patties.
Cook to a golden brown on both sides. Yields about 14.

title: gazpacho
directions: Cut off crusts of bread and cut into small cubes.
Mix oil and vinegar; pour over bread while chopping vegetables.
In a large container put all the chopped vegetables.
Add tomato and V-8 juices and garlic cloves or garlic juice.
Add bread cubes. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve cold.
A family recipe.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Scald tomatoes with chopped onions and peppers. Cook one hour; add pinch of garlic.
Add spices, oil, sugar, salt and tomato paste.
Cook another hour.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour muffin tins (or spray with Pam).
Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Cream the butter and sugar together with an electric mixer. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
By hand, blend milk into batter alternately with dry ingredients. Stir in berries. Toss lemon peel with sugar. Pour batter into tins.
Sprinkle with sugared lemon peel. Bake 25 minutes or until tops are golden. Can be frozen after baking. Makes 24 medium muffins.

title: date applesauce cake
directions: In saucepan, bring applesauce to boil and baking soda and cut up dates.
Set aside to cool.
In large bowl, cream shortening and 1 cup sugar (reserve 2 tablespoons for topping).
Stir applesauce, flour, chocolate chips and nuts together in bowl with shortening and sugar mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar, chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Rinse noodles in cold water.
Stir in remaining ingredients with noodles.

title: burritos dough
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Add shortening.
Mix until like corn meal.
Add 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix.
Add 1 tablespoon more at a time until it forms a ball.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Shape into a ball.
Roll on a lightly floured surface until round shape forms thin.
Fry in frypan at medium heat until lightly browned or about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: creamy caramel dip
directions: Microwave caramels
and cream in 1 quart bowl on High 4 to 5 minutes
or
until dip is smooth, stirring every minute. Serve warm with fruit, angel food or pound cake cubes.
For an added touch,
add tablespoon of almond, coffee or Irish cream flavored liqueur.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble raw beef in mixing bowl.
Stir in onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Cut bread into cubes; moisten with milk.
Add to beef mixture.
Blend in ketchup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
May be doubled.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind the cucumbers and onions; mix together with salt (juice and all).
Let drain for 20 minutes.
Mix together celery seed, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, allspice and turmeric.
Bring to a boil. Add the drained cucumbers and onions; boil again and let simmer 5 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and process in water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 pints.

title: spinach and lentil soup
directions: Place chicken and water in a large soup pot.
While water is coming to a boil, add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
After 1 hour, remove chicken from bones and discard bone and skin.
Return chicken meat to soup mixture for the last 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Chop tomatoes in cubes.
Chop lettuce finely.
Grate cheese. Cream together taco seasoning, sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread refried beans on the bottom of pan.
Add sour cream and cream cheese mixture.
Spread on top of refried beans.
Spread picante sauce on top of sour cream and cream cheese mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a jelly roll pan (4 sided baking sheet).
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Make graham cracker crust in spring-form pan.
Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Beat until mixed, then add sour cream and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until mixed. Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 400° for exactly 30 minutes.
Cool before serving.
Do not mix any more than necessary.

title: chicken crouton casserole
directions: Lay chicken pieces in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir together broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle croutons on top. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4 people.

title: cream cheese cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Once cream cheese is softened, mix all ingredients together in large mixer bowl.
Grease a 9-inch glass pie plate with butter.
Pour batter into pie plate.
Bake for 50 minutes.
When cool, add about 3/4 of cherry pie filling to top of pie.

title: buttermilk pancakes or waffles
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and salad oil.
Add flour sifted with salt, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Beat well.
Fold in egg whites.
Makes 6 waffles.

title: fudge upside-down cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix coconut and pecans together.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mom's fruit cocktail bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy, then add fruit cocktail. To egg mixture add flour, soda and salt small amount at a time until well blended, then add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on greased and floured cookie sheet 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inches.
Frost as desired.
Cut into bars when cooled.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. For chewy cookies, use slightly less sugar.
When doubling the recipe, add an extra egg.

title: sue charles' broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned in an 8 x 13-inch sprayed baking dish.
You may have to add water to make mixture the consistency of cornbread.

title: microwave avalanche appetizer
directions: Lay out Doritos chips on serving platter.
Heat chili in bowl in microwave 1 to 2 minutes (High).
Cover with paper towel.
Heat Cheez Whiz in microwave in its jar (remove lid), 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (High).
When chili and cheese are heated, pour chili over Doritos, then pour melted cheese over that.
Scatter pepper rings and sliced olives over the top.

title: apple-nut stuffed pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch skillet, melt 1/2 cup butter until sizzling; add onion.
Cook over medium heat until tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts, apple, water and stuffing.
Fill pockets in pork chops with stuffing.
In same skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Brown pork chops on both sides; place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover; bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until no longer pink and thermometer reaches 170°. Makes 6 servings.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Form meat balls and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate slush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave and add Ro-Tel and mix.
Serve with corn chips.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Let cool completely.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Cut fruit into cubes.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yields about 2 cups. Serves 25 to 30.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop onto greased cookie sheet. Press down.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool on waxed paper.

title: old fashioned cucumber and onion pickles
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat, stirring, just until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Arrange cucumbers and onion in a covered refrigerated dish.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Stir and serve.

title: blondie chip brownies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey apricot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix egg, milk, honey and margarine.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Stir in cereal and apricots.
Pour into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan which has been sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Makes 16 (1/2-inch) slices.
For easier slicing, wrap bread and store overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and crabmeat together.
Mix cream cheese, onion, salt, pepper, milk, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish together.
Then add crabmeat.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: quick party mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; stir well. Place in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: denver sandwich ring
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine pancake mix, oil, milk and egg. Stir by hand until blended. Stir in ham, onion and pepper; mix well. Drop by heaping tablespoons in a ring around edge of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 425° for 15 or 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: katie whittley's great cake
directions: Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Heat oil, cook garlic and onion until soft. Add beef and seasonings, cook until crumbly.
Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend eggs with cottage or Ricotta cheese.

title: chicken birdies
directions: Divide chipped beef in eight equal parts, then place an equal part on a flattened chicken breast and wrap the chicken breast around the beef.
Wrap the half slice of bacon around the "rolled" breast and secure with a toothpick.
Place the eight wrapped breasts in a buttered casserole.

title: rum dum diddy
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add beans and ketchup (needs to be very soupy).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: special holiday pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together pumpkin, honey, oil, eggs and almond extract in a blender.
Pour into large mixing bowl and sift flour and other dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Stir well.
Add nuts and raisins to mixture.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Mix other ingredients in another bowl.
Mix together both mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May flour and grease two 9-inch cake pans or one 13 x 9-inch long pan.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Saute
ground
beef,
peppers
and onion.
Add eggs and cook until
eggs
are
done.
Into a greased casserole, put a layer
of meat, a layer of corn and a layer of sliced tomato. Continue
in this fashion until all ingredients are gone.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour large tube pan.
Preheat oven to 300°. Cream butter and sugar together in large bowl.
Pour the milk in cup and add flavoring to milk.
Stir together.
Add 1 egg at a time, alternating with flour slowly, until completely blended. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and reserve half. Mix in rice and vegetables.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top and cover with reserved sauce. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° for 75 to 90 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato-carrot kugel
directions: Toss together the potatoes, carrots and onions. Stir the eggs and oil; add to vegetables. Blend in the matzoh meal.
Pour into well-greased 3-quart casserole or loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to eggs and mix.
Add corn and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sit in pan with inch of water surrounding dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1 /2 hours until set.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies(low-fat)
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Shape dough by tablespoon into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of floured glass.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done. Remove from baking sheets and cool on wire racks.

title: florentine beef(casserole)
directions: Brown beef, onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano in a heavy frying pan over medium to high heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in flour.
Add beef broth and cook until thickened.
Stir in sour cream.
Add drained spinach.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool 15 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 425°.

title: chop suey
directions: Salt and
pepper
meat, then roll in flour and deep fry until golden brown.
Be sure oil is hot, then place in pan and cover with foil.	Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie casserole
directions: Cook complete package frozen mixed vegetables in 5 cups chicken broth and 2 tablespoons chopped onion for 5 minutes. Thicken with flour, mixed with 1 cup milk.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour half of mixture into 2 1/2-quart casserole; cover with layer of chicken and then add remaining vegetable mixture.
Arrange small rounds of biscuit dough, about 1/2-inch thick over top.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuit dough is golden brown.
If less than full contents of package are used, modify ingredients accordingly.

title: holiday coffee
directions: Make dough: Sprinkle yeast and a pinch of sugar over warm water in measuring cup.
Stir.
Let stand just until foamy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Meanwhile, whisk together 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and cardamom in large bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour mixture until coarse crumbs form.
Whisk together lukewarm milk, 2 eggs and egg yolk in medium bowl until blended: whisk in other ingredients and knead.
Let rise.
Press one piece of dough into a 16 X 9 inch rectangle onto a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Cut twelve 1-inch strips of dough along each side of filling.
Gently stretch strips across filling; alternating side to side and pressing gently. Roll two 16-inch-long ropes of dough.
Join one end of ropes and twist together: arrange down center of loaf.

title: hot egg nog
directions: Cream egg yolks and sugar well.
Bring milk to a boil.
Stir in 1/2 cup to creamed mixture, stirring constantly.
Add creamed mixture to hot milk.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold into milk and creamed mixture.
Add rum extract.
Serve hot with sprinkled nutmeg on top.
Rum may be substituted for rum extract.

title: baked ham sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, mustard, mayonnaise and poppy seed together. Spread liberally on both sides of buns.
Place ham, cheese and onion on rolls.
Wrap airtight in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Can be made ahead and then baked later.

title: more
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add onion, green peppers and celery.
Cook slowly for several minutes.
Add noodles.
Add tomato sauce, corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Turn into baking dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham cheese log
directions: Beat cheeses together.
Add ham and beat.
Stir in olives. Chill 20 minutes.
Shape into two 8-inch logs.
Roll in pecans and serve with crackers.
Logs can be frozen.
Thaw 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large soup pot, brown meat; drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, basil, seasoned salt and onion soup mix.
Stir in boiling water, tomato sauce and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add celery, celery leaves, carrots and split peas or lentils.
Continue to cook 30 minutes.
Add macaroni, zucchini and spinach; simmer 30 minutes longer, adding water if necessary. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on individual servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in bowl; add Miracle Whip (use as much or as little as you like). Makes a medium size bowl of salad.

title: steve's special sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Wonderful on chicken legs or wings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice onion and zucchini.
In frypan, saute onion until tender in oil.
Add zucchini; toss until tender.
Add stewed tomatoes; cover for 5 minutes.
Transfer to casserole dish.
When ready to bake, shake on cheese and reheat until ready to serve.

title: chicken
directions: Wrap dried beef around chicken and then wrap bacon around the dried beef.
Layer in oblong dish.
Mix the sour cream, wine and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken breasts and sprinkle with paprika and fresh mushrooms (optional).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: better egg custard
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Melt butter in pie plate, pour in mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, extract and salt.
Blend in sour cream.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and enough milk until stiff enough to drop in a deep fryer.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper, salt and onion; drain off fat and add 1 cup water and beans together.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan and layer the sour cream, cheese and taco sauce.
Place black olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve as a dip for Doritos or corn chips.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Salt to taste. Serves 5 or 6.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: kielbasa stew
directions: Cut kielbasa into 2-inch pieces.
Add a little sugar.
Cook 1/2 hour.
When done, add 1 can peas and butter.

title: low-fat chicken-chile rolls
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place a green chile half and 1 cheese strip in center of each breast half.
Roll breast lengthwise; tuck ends under and secure with wooden picks.

title: chicken salad(also good with turkey)
directions: Mix all together.
Serve on buns or bread or dice whole tomato and add scoop of salad to top.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour, salt, eggs, and fruit juices; cook until thick then cool.
Combine pasta with cooked mixture.
Add pineapple, mandarin oranges, marshmallows, coconut and cool whip.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Cook until tender.
Drain well; set aside, then mix half and half, water, cheese and seasoning into boiler.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted, then add cornstarch mixture and broccoli. Cook until soup is thickened.
Serve hot.

title: apple pie
directions: Place bottom crust in pie pan. Layer sliced apples into pan. Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle on apples. Dot butter on top of mixture, then put top crust on. Brush top crust with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Cut slits in top crust. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Heat sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa until ingredients boil.
Then add remaining ingredients and drop on greased cookie sheets (cool).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
This is a must.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Add butter (1 tablespoon) and cool.
Pour over unmolded cake.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on the package.
Cut broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, cucumber and tomatoes into nice large chunks into a medium-sized bowl.
Add pasta and about 3/4 of the Italian dressing.
Stir thoroughly.
Add more dressing until desired taste.
To easily turn this into a seafood pasta salad, add a small can of either shrimp or minced crab meat to your pasta salad.
Chill before serving.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Boil berries, water, cinnamon, sugar and vanilla on high heat. Blend on medium-high speed the flour, shortening and milk.
Roll out onto floured board; roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares and drop into boiling mixture.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir slowly. Let boil for additional 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let cool for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: jam fruit cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift spices,
flour
and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to flour mixture.
Put raisins, nuts, candied fruits, figs and dates in flour mixture.
Add jam.
Bake approximately 2 hours at 250° (you might need to put a pan of water under bottom of cake to keep it from getting too hard).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and cover with either Miracle Whip or Zesty Italian dressing.

title: tuna ala king
directions: Heat soup in saucepan.
Add chopped, hard-boiled eggs, pimento and tuna.
Peel the crust from 12 slices of bread.
Gently press into muffin tin.
Fill bread with tuna mixture.
Grate the remaining egg yolk and garnish each cup.
Place in hot oven at 400°.
Leave only until bread is toasted.
Good for ladies' luncheons.
Serve with salad.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the butter, sugar, cocoa and milk over medium heat; when smooth, take off heat.
Add the peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Put in pan and chill.

title: hot squash
directions: Saute onion and pepper in large heavy skillet; add diced onion and diced tomatoes.
Add sliced squash and water.
Cook slowly in open skillet until liquid has cooked down.
Sprinkle cheese on top; cover and let stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: steamed vegetable night
directions: A variety of steamed fresh vegetables served with cole slaw makes a wonderful fat free meal.
Serve with hot brown rice or bulgur (cracked wheat).
Cole slaw is made with nonfat dressing.

title: pecan pie tarts
directions: Soften cheese and butter; blend in flour.
Chill 1 hour. Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Press into ungreased muffin pan. Put 1 teaspoon of filling in center (after pressing dough up a little around sides).

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in small loaves or one large loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: john torrey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Spray skillet with a nonstick coating.
Add ground beef, green pepper and onion. Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, including macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
(May add other spices that you like.)
One serving: 1 cup.
Calories per serving: 220.
Exchanges: 1 medium fat meat, 1 1/2 starch and 1 vegetable.

title: applesauce raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add berries, stirring until thawed.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Pour beaten eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla into casserole and mix. Add bread; allow to soak 10 to 15 minutes, then stir well, breaking up bread. Add melted butter and stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is done. Serve with chocolate sauce, whipped cream or any other topping.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix in large bowl and store in jars.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons to cup of boiling water.

title: chicken fritters
directions: Mix egg yolks, chicken, celery and leaves, onion, flour and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Drop from large spoon into hot oil; brown on both sides.
Serve with gravy.

title: cranberry juice cocktail
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, if needed.
Serve in cocktail glasses topped with a scoop of lemon or lime sherbet on top as a first course cocktail.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough flour to make stiff.
Roll in teaspoon size balls and press flat with fingers on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: good cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake according to box directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; cool.
Poke holes in top of cake with fork. Pour 1 can crushed pineapple (juice and all) over top of cake. Prepare instant pudding and spread over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Place all ingredients, except jello, into a small saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Allow to boil for approximately 12 minutes, or until pineapple is tender.
Stir frequently. Remove from heat; pour in the strawberry jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars; let cool for 30 minutes, then cover.

title: potatoes and peas
directions: Wash small potatoes well.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and add onion in skillet and saute until brown.
Return bacon bits to pan.	Add potatoes.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add water as needed to keep from sticking.
Add cooked peas and cream.
Simmer for a short time.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients one at a time.
Beat egg whites slightly and fold in mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spaghetti - pizza style
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Toss with cooked spaghetti. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with spaghetti sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Add chopped vegetables and boil 3 minutes.
Can in hot jars and seal at once.
Makes 9 to 10 pints.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs; toss lightly together.
Pour into a 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole (flat works best).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, until bread crumbs are brown and mixture is bubbly.

title: bacon-cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and place in saucepan.
Cover with water and cook until tender, but firm.
Drain and cube.
Mix potatoes with onion, cheese and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Transfer mixture to ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cookie fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough and place close together on oblong pan. Sprinkle lightly with regular sugar.
Bake until lightly brown. Mix cream cheese and sugar together until smooth and spread over cooled cookie crust.
Spread 1/3 of glaze over cream cheese mixture.
Place fruit; put bananas on first, pineapples, oranges, blueberries and then strawberries.
Pour remainder of glaze over fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Chill 6 hours before serving.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and cut zucchini into slices; peel and cut onion into quarters, then slice very thin.
Add to zucchini.
Sprinkle zucchini and onion with salt; add cold water to cover.
Let stand for 2 hours; drain.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour over zucchini and onion.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Bring all ingredients to boiling point; heat 5 minutes.
Pack hot into jars; process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: tuna and sauerkraut
directions: Saute onion in butter until softened.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Mix in bread crumbs.
Blend well.
Mix in remaining ingredients and place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into 6 patties.
In skillet, over medium-high heat, cook patties, a few at a time, until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, spices and oil.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in a warm oven (250°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through cooking.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, water and salt until thickens.
Add Jell-O and strawberries.
Pour into 2 graham cracker shells.
Cook, then add Cool Whip on top.

title: frozen custard(makes 5 quarts)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Add a small amount of hot mixture to beaten eggs, mix well and return this to hot mixture. Stir 1 minute.
Take off heat and chill.
When custard is cooled, add cream and vanilla; freeze in freezer.
This is so-o-o good!

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours; garnish.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Heat 1/2 inch of oil in skillet and fry tortillas about 15 seconds each side; remove and pat off excess oil.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion soup mix and stir in, add water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and cover.
Simmer until rice is tender.
Good with soy sauce or Worcestershire sauce.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a large saucepan over low heat, stir together the first 3 ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 32.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and peanut butter together.
Put mixed ingredients in crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: dump cake
directions: Do not mix together.
Pour ingredients into ungreased pan in layers.
Cut butter into pats and put on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake springs back.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Place celery in baking dish; cover with plastic wrap and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Combine water, butter and stuffing.
In a 12 x 8-inch casserole, layer celery, meat and stuffing.
Pour soup over top, spreading evenly. Cover and microwave 8 minutes, turning dish one-half turn after 4 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir meal into rapidly boiling milk.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
The mixture will be cold and stiff.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Beat with electric beater for 15 minutes.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: bake sale cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a plastic
or paper bag. Shake to mix and set aside.
Combine
buttermilk	and
baking powder
in a bowl and mix well.
Dip 2 pieces	of
chicken
in buttermilk mixture; place chicken in bag of flour and shake to coat.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken.
Place chicken in a shallow pan; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat 1-inch
of oil in a large skillet to 325°
or
medium-high
on stove.
Add chicken and fry 30 to 35 minutes
or
until golden brown, turning only once. Drain on paper towel.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown the ground beef, drain, add sauce and simmer.
Cook and drain lasagne noodles.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt and the oregano.
Reserve 1/2 cup meat sauce for thin top layer.

title: cherry-pineapple cake
directions: Chop or slice cherries and add 1/2 can crushed, drained pineapple to cake batter.
Follow directions on cake mix.
Bake according to directions.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: How easy!
Add a few ingredients to a potato mix and in 30 minutes, serve a hearty soup.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Roll each biscuit piece in mixture.
Place in a greased Bundt pan. Melt butter, water and white sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Eat while hot.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix in blender.
Serve over fruit of the season in glass goblets.

title: salsa dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour salsa over cream cheese, then spread.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over salsa.
Bake at 350° until Mozzarella cheese is melted. Remove from oven.
Serve with nachos.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken bake
directions: Bake chicken skinned and cube it.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add water and dressing mix.
In large bowl, mix rice, soup, milk, chicken and sauteed mixture.
Place in casserole and cover with sliced almonds.
Bake at 32° for 30 minutes.

title: avery island hot corn bread
directions: 1. Stir together dry ingredients. Add everything else.
2. Beat just till smooth. Bake in 425° for 20-30 or top is golden.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook over medium heat until golden brown and stringy. Take off heat and add butter, salt and baking soda.
Mix well and pour into buttered pans.

title: zucchini parmigiana
directions: Saute zucchini in olive oil.
Add rest of ingredients, except for Mozzarella cheese.
Simmer until zucchini is cooked.
Add sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: d's dixie-delight chocolate gravy
directions: Put water and milk in iron skillet.
Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in bowl.
Stir in the skillet before the water and milk get very hot.
When gravy thickens somewhat, add vanilla and butter. Pour over hot biscuits.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Combine soup, onion, eggs, cheese and mayonnaise. Fold until mixed thoroughly. Layer broccoli and sauce in a greased casserole. May add buttered bread crumbs. Place in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: self-crust chicken pie
directions: Place chicken
in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer egg slices on this.
Blend
broth and soup in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour
broth
and
soup
mixture
over meat and egg slices.
Mix margarine,	flour, milk and pepper and pour over ingredients
in baking dish.
This mixture will not be smooth. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: mrs. wyatt's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add 2 eggs alternately with 1 cup flour, mixing well until all are used.
Add cream; beat until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O, 2 cups water and sugar.
Heat until dissolved.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Chill.
Can be frozen.
Serves 16.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter on high.
Add the bag of marshmallows and melt. Pour the Rice Krispies in the pan and stir.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: blueberry-yogurt muffins(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Gently fold in blueberries.
Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin cups coated with cooking spray; sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar evenly over muffins.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans immediately; let cool on a wire rack.
Calories:
3.4 grams.

title: peanut butter and chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine peanut butter and butter.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until blended and fluffy.
Add flour and salt.
Beat until blended. Beat in 1/2 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
While bars are hot, sprinkle remaining chips evenly over bars.
Let stand 2 minutes or until chips are melted.
Pull a knife through the chips to make a pattern on the bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: cody's favorite pizza toast
directions: Place slices of bread on baking sheet or pizza pan.
Spread 1 or 2 tablespoons sauce on each piece.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of Cheddar and 1/4 cup of Mozzarella cheese on each piece.
Then top with other pizza toppings of your choice such as pepperoni, green peppers, onions. etc.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes, until bottom of bread is brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Best if mixed 2 to 3 hours before using.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop cheese in small chunks, pinch up lettuce in small pieces, chop tomatoes and place these in a large bowl.
Add 1 can beans. Mix well, add Catalina dressing and toss well.
Place in refrigerator until just before serving.
Add Fritos, toss well and serve.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and milk to boiling point.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and spread on cooled cake when frosting has cooled.

title: yellow straightneck squash
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese and salt together.
Slice squash 1/4-inch thick.
Coat both sides with mayonnaise and dip in coating mixture.
Place in 9 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: pizza cups
directions: Cool meat and put biscuits into muffin tins with mix and cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pie crust in a pan
directions: With a fork, mix the dry ingredients in a pie pan.
Form a well in the center and pour the oil and milk into the center.
Mix well with a fork and press to bottom and up sides.
Prick the bottom.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add half of flour and half of milk alternately, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating next half of the flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Put into cold oven at 325° for 1 hour, then turn to 350° for 1/2 hour.
Do not open oven until you take cake out.
Set pan on damp cloth for 5 minutes.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Melt butter, stir in sugar and flour until well blended. Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk, add eggs, and baking powder.
Mix well.
Fold in corn.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole, a low flat dish works best.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: wild rice casserole a la peggy
directions: Soak wild rice in warm water for 2 hours, rinsing water several times.
Drain.
In a pot, have 3 quarts of water boiling (part of liquid could be chicken stock); add rice.
Bring to boil. Turn off heat and let it stand, covered, 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute first four ingredients together. Add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into greased oblong pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter custard pie
directions: Combine confectioners sugar and peanut butter; blend well. Spread 3/4 of this mixture on bottom of baked pie shell.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk and mix well.
Pour small amount over egg yolks.
Mix well, then return to milk mixture.
Cook in top of double boiler over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla, then pour into prepared pastry shell.
Top with meringue.

title: apple sheet pie
directions: Dribble this on top of pie.

title: garden harvest chili
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium-high.
Saute garlic, peppers, mushrooms and onion until tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, tomato sauce, chili powder, sugar and cumin; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; add beans, zucchini and corn. Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes, until zucchini is tender. Spoon into bowls; sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Beat well.
Add syrup, vanilla, margarine and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Meanwhile, combine 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour this batter over melted butter.
Then empty entire can of peaches and juice on top of batter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery to bacon drippings along with garlic and cook until tender.
Add soups, mushrooms, diced chicken and seasonings and simmer until hot. Crumble bacon into this and stir well.
Cook spaghetti and drain well.
In casserole pan layer spaghetti, then sauce mix.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: nutty sour cream orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners or grease 12 muffin cups.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt one stick of butter or margarine in Pyrex dish and add sugar, baking powder, flour and milk.
Pour 2 cups of fruit on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes, until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
With fork dipped in flour, flatten in crisscross pattern to 2 inches. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until set.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine dry soup, Russian dressing and jam, mixing well until there are no lumps.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Slightly overlap in flat pyrex dish.
Spoon and spread 1 Tbsp. or more of sauce on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 225 degrees for 4 to 5 hours or however long it takes to get done.
Be careful to place well below heating element if using electric oven.
This can be done in 1 hour at 375 degrees.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas in oil in fry pan, on both sides, for just a few seconds.
Do not brown.
Stack on paper towels to drain.
Mix together chicken soup, sour cream, chilies, and grated cheese (save a cup or so for the topping).
Mix part of sauce mixture with chicken to moisten.
Fill tortillas with this mixture and roll, place seam side down in greased 9x13-inch (or larger) pan. Cover with remaining sauce, mixture, and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes, covered with foil.
Uncover for the last 5 minutes. This can be made ahead and refrigerated, and leftovers can be frozen.
Top with salsa to make spicier!

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Stir the ingredients with a fork.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup more of flour onto waxed paper.
Knead and pat down to about 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits with a circular cutter or roll out with hands.
Place on greased baking sheets and bake about 10 to 15 minutes at 400° or until brown.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Butter the sides of a 2-quart microproof bowl.
Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and margarine in bowl.
Do not stir.
Microwave on 7 for 15 minutes.
Stir just to mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and continue on 7 to soft ball (235°).
Add vanilla; beat to soft peaks and pour in rounds over pecans on greased tray or foil. Very rich, but great.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown together beef, pork, onion and celery.
Combine with rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Excellent to freeze and bake later.

title: grandma's oatmeal crispies
directions: Beat eggs until light, adding other ingredients.
Mix well. Form into 3 log shaped rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until next day.
Slice 1/4 inch thick pieces.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dump the cherry pie filling and drained pineapple into the greased baking dish.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the top of the filling and pineapple.
Pour the melted butter over the top of the yellow cake mix.
Sprinkle the chopped nuts and shredded coconut over the top of the whole thing.
Put into the oven and bake for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 12 to 14 pieces.

title: cherry cha cha
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add butter and sugar.
Take out 2 tablespoons.
Press the rest down firmly in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill.
Whip cream.
Add marshmallows carefully.
Put half of mixture on chilled crust.
Put the cherry pie filling on.
Add remaining mixture.
Top with 2 tablespoons crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot peas
directions: Combine peas and tomatoes.
In medium skillet, melt margarine and saute last 3 ingredients.
Add sauteed vegetables to the pea mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into serving dish, cover and chill until served.
This dish is best served at room temperature as if it were a salad.

title: 7-up cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat the butter at medium speed until creamed.
Gradually add the sugar; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour; beat well. Add butter extract, 7-Up and lemon extract; beat just until thoroughly blended.
Turn batter into prepared 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pirate's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large skillet, melt shortening. Add beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook, stirring with a fork to break apart meat, until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes. Add beans and pimento.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: burnt sugar(old fashioned louisiana candy)
directions: You will need waxed paper and a greased rolling pin for this recipe.

title: cucumber namasu
directions: Partly peel cucumbers, leaving narrow strips of peel.
Thinly slice cucumbers.
In a measuring cup or mixing bowl, combine vinegar, sugar, salt and ginger root; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumber slices.
Cover and chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in iron skillet. Add pineapple. Decorate with cherries. Pour in batter.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
