Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix well and bring to boiling point.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Pour over popcorn and let cool to warm enough to handle.
Form into balls.

title: tupperware gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen block of fruit and stir gently until fruit has separated.
Beat with eggbeater for one minute.
Pour into Jel-N-Serve or individual serving molds.
Seal and chill until set firm.
Unmold and serve.

title: chicken breasts with wild rice
directions: Place bacon on bottom of a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place rice over bacon. Reserve package of seasonings. Place chicken on rice, bone down. Pour soup over the chicken, then add water. Top with seasonings package. Cover and cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Check toward the end to be sure rice is cooked, but not too dry. Serves 4.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in a dish; pour water over them.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut margarine into flour mixture.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: wonderful little biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into miniature muffin tins, ungreased.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes until crisp and golden.
These freeze well and reheat easily in microwave.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature. Mix all except mushrooms. Remove stems from mushrooms. Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Broil until cheese mixture is bubbly.

title: oreo dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt butter; crush Oreos and press on top of butter.

title: creamy potatoes and broccoli
directions: Arrange potatoes in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam 5 minutes; add broccoli, cover and steam 6 minutes.
Add mushrooms; cover and steam 3 minutes.
Remove the steamer from heat and uncover.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in sour cream, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Combine vegetables and sauce, stirring to coat.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of large Pyrex or other baking dish. Spread coconut over pineapple.
Spread cake mix over coconut. Spread nuts over cake mix.* Chip butter or oleo over the top. Place in 350° oven (more or less, depending on your oven) and cook 45 minutes.
Cook and serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: heaven delight
directions: In large bowl, mix marshmallows and fruit cocktail.
Put whipping cream and vanilla in deep bowl; whip until it peaks. Don't overbeat!
Pour whipped cream over fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Fold in evenly.

title: mince pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spread in pastry shell.
Top with second crust; seal edges and crimp.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cool. Serves 8.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except tortilla chips. Heat thoroughly over medium-high heat until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with the tortilla chips.
Yields 3 cups.

title: almond biscotti
directions: Butter and flour cookie sheet.
Chop chocolate.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add almond paste and butter (don't overmix).
Add almonds, nuts and chopped chocolate.
Mix eggs (save 2 tablespoons).
Add vanilla to eggs, then add to previous mixture in a "well" in center of dry mix.
Form into a ball.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Blend oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, to oil and sugar mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Slightly melt cream cheese frosting in microwave.
Pour 1/2 container over top of cake "to frost".

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir in tomato paste, water, salt and tomatoes.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Line dish with layer of noodles, sauce and cheese, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
(Serves 8 to 10.)

title: caramel chewies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan. Remove from heat.
Add sugar. Stir well. Do not use electric mixer!
Add vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares when cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix together and simmer 1 hour or more.

title: grandma rodine's carrot and cucumber relish
directions: Combine ground vegetables and salt.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Seal at once.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: texas barbecued cheeseburgers
directions: In a small bowl, combine soy sauce, chili powder and garlic pepper.
Shape ground beef into 4 patties.
Brush both sides of patties with soy sauce mixture.
Preheat grill or broiler.
Grill or broil 4 to 5 minutes per side or until desired doneness.
Top each burger with 2 tablespoons cheese and cook until melted. Serve on hamburger buns and top as desired.
Serves 4.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Grease lightly a 9 x 12 inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with crumbs.
Combine sugar and soft butter.
Cream well.
Add 2 very well beaten eggs.
Mix for at least 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Spread raspberries evenly over mixture. Whip heavy cream, 3 Tablespoons powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over raspberries.
Top with remaining crumbs.

title: marie's cherry almond drops
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
In nonsifted flour, add salt and soda and stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients and mix well.
Add maraschino cherries (cut in small pieces).
Add the coconut and almond flavoring.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: turkette
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma foster's fudge icing
directions: Cook together until boiling.
Beat in 1 box powdered sugar until thick.
Great on chocolate cake.

title: mary's cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together until well blended.
Then add flour, soda, tartar and salt.
When well mixed add oats, rice krispies, coconut and nuts.
Roll into 9 dozen 1 inch balls.
Press down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar, mixing well.
Heat margarine, Coca-Cola and cocoa to boiling point.
Pour over flour mixture, beating well.
Pour into ungreased and floured sheet cake pan. Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool slightly.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Makes 1 cup.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix sour cream and milk together thoroughly.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to the milk mixture.
Stir until all is moistened.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into paper muffin cups, which have been placed in muffin tins.
Freeze.
Remove paper cups from tin and store in plastic bag or cover.
Remove paper from salad before serving.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pasta with vegetables
directions: Boil for 8 to 10 minutes the pasta in large pot with oil and salt.
Drain.
Steam vegetables for 4 to 6 minutes.
Toss olive oil, herbs, salt and pepper with vegetables and pasta.
Cover with cheese.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Simmer onion in oil until it turns, then add remaining ingredients (except beans and water) and cook for 15 minutes.
Add beans and water.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let butter, margarine and cream cheese get real soft.
Mix until well blended.
Add sugar until blended.
Add baking powder and vanilla extract, making sure all ingredients are mixed well. Add eggs and flour and mix very well.
Set oven at 325° and bake until done.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup peppers and 1/2 cup onions.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add beans and 1/4 pound cheese; continue cooking until cheese is melted.	Dip tortillas in hot oil (a few drops of oil for each in a skillet warming on both sides).
Fill each tortilla with approximately 1/4 cup meat mixture; roll up.	Please seam side down in 12 x 8 baking dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and continue baking uncovered 5 minutes.
Top with remaining onions, peppers and tomatoes. Can be served with sour cream and lettuce.
We also have Spanish rice on the side.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix; pour into greased dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese potato salad
directions: Mix together sour cream and dressing; add potatoes and eggs. Allow to marinate while preparing rest of ingredients.
Fold in cottage cheese, celery, olives, radishes, onions and salt.
Pack into ring mold.
Chill; unmold onto lettuce.
Put vegetable stick relishes in the center.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Put into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: the general
directions: Mix well and place in a 2-quart casserole or 2 smaller baking dishes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain.
Add onion and garlic. Saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, oregano and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Layer half the noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Velveeta and Parmesan cheese in an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: blue cheese appetizers
directions: Cut uncooked biscuits into quarters.
Arrange biscuits in a round cake pan.
Combine butter and cheese in saucepan and heat until melted.
Pour over biscuits.
Heat at 350 for 15 minutes or until cooked and liquid is absorbed.

title: apple bars
directions: Cut margarine into flour and salt until looks like small peas. Add enough milk to beaten egg yolk to measure 2/3 cup.
Stir into flour mixture until cleans side of bowl.
Divide into 2 parts. Roll one part into 10 x 15-inch rectangle.
Fold into thirds and place in jelly roll pan.
Unfold.
Sprinkle crushed Wheaties over pastry.

title: apple relish
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients. Put in a large saucepan, add other ingredients and let come to a boil. Boil for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Put mixture into hot sterilized pint jars and seal.

title: baked eggs and ham
directions: Toss croutons with melted butter, set aside.
Break eggs into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Top with cheese. Arrange ham on top.
Place buttered croutons around edge of dish. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees until eggs are done, 15 to 18 minutes.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute chicken in 1 tablespoon oil until done.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add cubed cheese.
Soften flour tortillas in oil.
Spoon ingredients into tortilla.
Roll and fasten with toothpick.
Excellent to freeze for use later.
Thaw completely, then heat in microwave.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine soup, cheese and milk. Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in chicken, chilies, tomato sauce and onion in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Repeat layers, ending with cheese mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix cheese, sour cream, green chili peppers and taco seasoning mix together.
Chill at least 2 hours in the refrigerator before serving.
Makes 3 cups or 24 servings.

title: onion and cucumber relish
directions: In container, stir together vinegar, water, sugar and salt. Pare cucumbers thinly.
Run sharp tines of a fork lengthwise down the cucumbers to score, slice very thin.
Peel onions and slice thin, separate into rings.
Add cucumbers and onions to marinate. Cover.
Chill at least a couple of hours before serving.
Leave vegetables in marinade and use a pierced or slotted serving spoon. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: strawberries n' yogurt
directions: Make several hours ahead.
Wash, hull and drain berries.
Can slice if you wish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into dessert dishes or glasses and refrigerate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swordfish mediterranean
directions: In 12-inch skillet, saute oil, onion and garlic. Add all else, except the fish.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Make layers for first 3 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine milk, salt, pepper and eggs.
Pour over layers.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: california casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Place in bottom of a large baking dish or divide into 2 smaller ones if you want to freeze one.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Combine and sift flour, soda and baking powder. Fold into batter.
Add vanilla.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and extract.
Beat well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours. Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on pan before removing to a wire rack.
Yield:
5 1/2 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: rhubarb crunch(serves 9)
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Place half the flour mixture in a 9-inch square pan. Add rhubarb. Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and flavoring.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb and cover with remaining flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook until thickened.
Add lump of butter and let cool.
Put in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 3 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Top pie and brown in 350° oven.

title: gracie's raised donuts
directions: Mix yeast and warm milk in bowl.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Let rise in warm spot until it has doubled in bulk. Cream Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add egg.
Add to raised flour and yeast; add remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Let rise until it has doubled in bulk.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Let stand until it has doubled in size and fry off in Crisco.
Makes 24 and they are real good!
(Ask my kids.)

title: buckeye cookie
directions: Thoroughly mix oleo, sugar, vanilla and peanut butter.
Roll into small teaspoon size balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Keep on low heat while dipping balls.
Use a toothpick to dip balls.
Leave a small space open at top to give the appearance of a buckeye.
Put on wax paper to dry and refrigerate.

title: dolores cauliflower salad
directions: Cover lettuce and cauliflower with sugar and toss with just enough mayonnaise to coat.
Cover overnight in refrigerator and add remaining ingredients.
If desired, add frozen peas and let set.

title: low-fat raspberry chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Beat in skim milk and softened spread along with the vanilla extract until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar and beat.
Fold egg whites into cake mixture until smooth.
Pile into one or two well-greased and floured 9 or 10-inch round baking pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour if using one pan, or about 35 to 40 minutes if using two pans.
Remove and let cool.

title: nutty o's
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Heat sugar, syrup, butter and salt in three-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, about five minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.
Spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Loosen with metal spatula.
Let stand one hour.
Store in covered container.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: pennsylvania dutch sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into rolls or logs.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Sugar may be sprinkled on top before baking.
Keep batter cold between slicings.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Make it a family project to look up the ingredients.
All are found in the Bible (KJV).
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; add honey and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk; stir in raisins, figs and almonds.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour, juice and rind of lemon.
Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Add beaten egg whites gently to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is almost set.
Very good.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Melt butter. Add spices. Coat pecans in mixture. Toast at 375° until brown, about 20 minutes. Shake occasionally during toasting. Drain on paper towels.

title: lazy day chili
directions: Brown hamburger really well and pour off grease.
Add tomato sauce and 1 can of water to rinse cans.
Add beans and 1/2 can of water to rinse.
Stir frequently.
More water may be added, if desired.
Any seasoning may be added but we love it plain.

title: bacon wrap-ups
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Cut bread into 3 strips.
Generously spread undiluted soup on each strip.
Cut bacon strips in half. Place bread strip on half slice of bacon and roll together.
Place rolls on a rack, cookie sheet or broiler pan with sides to catch drippings.
Bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour or until crisp.
Makes 30 roll-ups.

title: chocolate-spice cookies
directions: Beat the egg whites until they are stiff and stand in peaks. Set aside.
Mix the chocolate and almonds.
Add the sugar and spices.
Blend well.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets, flatten.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 1/4 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Melt cheese and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Combine with sifted flour.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and pat thin on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or less until lightly browned.
Makes 75 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix the cheese into dough and spoon onto pan.
When done, melt butter, chives and garlic salt and brush on top of biscuits.

title: mound cake
directions: Make cake mix by package directions and bake.
Mix together remaining ingredients and cook until melted.
Mix well.
Yields filling for 3 layers.

title: aunt esther's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Make hole in middle of dry ingredients.
Drop egg in hole.
Add milk, oil, water and soda.
Mix gently.
Pour into glass loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple-peanut butter bars
directions: Combine margarine and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in apples and chips.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients and make into a roll.
Cover with wax and keep in refrigerator until chilled.
Then cut into slices and bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cool eggs.
Remove shells and cut into lengthwise halves. Remove yolks; mash with mayonnaise and remaining ingredients. Re-fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Yield: 12 halves.

title: spiced coffee
directions: Put the cold water in a 30-cup electric coffee maker.
Place the coffee, cinnamon sticks and cloves into the coffee-maker basket.
Prepare coffee according to manufacturer's directions. Makes about 24 (6 ounce) servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.	Mix all dry ingredients into shortening; mix.
Add dissolved yeast; mix and gradually add buttermilk.
Knead	dough
thoroughly.
Make
dough
into biscuits by hand or roll on a floured board and cut out.
Let rise	for
a short time.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Shred crabmeat.
Cut cheeses in small pieces.
Combine in saucepan with butter and Sauterne.
Stir over low heat until cheeses melt.
Stir in crabmeat and continue cooking until heated through.
Pour into chafing dish.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package; add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Pour over lime sherbet.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes (enough to cover broccoli).
Crumble Ritz crackers and melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in crackers and mix until coated.
Put crackers on top of cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° to 400°, until cheese starts to bubble, about 40 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all and cook 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° without opening oven door. Cook in Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.

title: wacky cake
directions: Into an ungreased pan, sift the flour, sugar, soda and cocoa. Make 3 holes in the dry ingredients.
Mix together the vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Pour this into the holes in equal amounts.
Over the whole thing, pour cold water.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, chili powder, sugar, salt and oregano.
Simmer 45 minutes; add beans.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Place by teaspoonfuls on a baking sheet and bake until golden brown on bottom of cookies.
These are very good cookies.
They also freeze well.

title: layered salad
directions: In a shallow salad bowl or 2-quart baking dish, layer all ingredients in the order given.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello-cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Mix sour cream, cranberries and pineapple with its juice.
Add to jello.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan or a salad mold.

title: everyone's favorite chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Spread with a buttercream frosting, dust with powdered sugar or drizzle with melted chocolate.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt half of butter; blend in flour until smooth.
Gradually add the chicken stock, stirring constantly to the boiling point. Add the pepper, cream, sherry and Swiss cheese.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
In a skillet, saute mushrooms 5 minutes in remaining butter.
Add cooked spaghetti and half the sauce.
Mix lightly.
Spread in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix the chicken with remaining sauce and pour over the spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fix Stove Top dressing according to directions.
Cook broccoli and chicken until almost done.
In casserole dish layer broccoli, chicken and dressing.
Save some dressing to put over top.
Add soup and milk; top with dressing.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until brown at 350°.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls into chicken broth.
Cook for 10 minutes in a covered pan, then for 10 minutes, uncovered, over medium heat.
Watch to make sure it doesn't get dry.
Add liquid if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
You can also add parsley flakes (dried) to flavor.

title: tomato soup spice cake
directions: First prepare pan.
Use either 1 (10-inch) round or 9-inch square pan.
Grease pan, then line completely with wax paper twice.
Cut a strip of heavy brown paper 1 inch taller than pan and long enough to go around outside of pan twice.
Tie it in place around pan with string.
Place double thickness of brown paper or newspaper on cookie sheet.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Place the torn lettuce in a large mixing bowl.
Then, in order in layers, add the chopped celery, chopped red onion, chopped green pepper and the peas.
Spread evenly with the salad dressing. Sprinkle the sugar over salad dressing.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over sugar.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Cover with Saran Wrap; chill overnight.
Serves 12.
(Recipe can be cut in half for smaller group.)

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and place in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on floured board and cut out biscuits.
Dip each biscuit in butter or pat buttermilk on each. Bake at 425° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup. Bring to boil and stir in jello.
Add partially thawed strawberries.
Stir until strawberries are thawed.
Add pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: empress green beans
directions: Cook celery in oleo until tender.
In separate pan blend cornstarch, chicken stock, soy sauce, sesame seed and garlic salt. Cook until thickened.
Combine both mixtures together.
Pour over drained green beans and parsley.
Heat thoroughly.

title: eggnog cheesecake(no-bake)
directions: In small mixing bowl combine the 1 1/4 cups crushed wafers and melted butter; toss thoroughly.
Press mixture into bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides of 1 (9-inch) spring-form pan to form a firm and even crust.
Chill about 1 hour or until firm.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and shallots in butter, tossing and stirring for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, blend well and cook for another minute or so.
Off heat, stir in broth and cream; return to the heat and stir until sauce thickens.
Add tarragon, wine and salt and pepper to taste.
Let bubble gently a few minutes until it is the consistency you want.
Serve over cooked chicken breasts.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening as pie dough and take out one cup for topping.
Add remaining ingredients; sprinkle crumbs on top and pour in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: jello tuna salad
directions: Dissolve the jello and salt in the boiling water.
Add the cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Add the mayonnaise, tuna and celery.
Pour into a 6-cup ring mold or any mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on crisp greens and a little mayonnaise.
Makes about 10 to 12 servings.

title: peppy pinto beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large Dutch oven.
Cover with water, 2-inches above beans.
Let soak 8 hours.
Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add water, chilies, garlic, chili powder and salt to beans.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.

title: juiced up chicken
directions: Season chicken (salt and pepper).
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix onion soup mix with juice.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water.
Combine liquids and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
(Given to me by my lovely daughter-in-law, Mindy Bess.)

title: egg salad
directions: Boil the eggs.
Mash eggs while mixing with other ingredients. Do not salt.
The salt in the crackers is enough.

title: sausage yummies
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain.
Open 2 cans crescent rolls. Remove from tube in 1 long piece and lay flat on baking pan. Pinch all of the perforations together and flatten.
Mix sausage and cream cheese together in a bowl.
Spread mixture over crescent rolls.
Top with 2 more cans of crescent rolls laid over the top. Bake at 375° until brown.
Cool and slice.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Add lemon juice and mix.
Stir in fruit.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Wait 15 minutes before serving.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni until tender. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix butter and elbow macaroni together.
Cut cheese in thick slices and mix with noodles.
Add enough milk to cover the cheese and noodles. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: lincoln & lee pudding
directions: Cook butter, water, brown sugar and vanilla in a saucepan together for 10 minutes. Combine flour, sugar and baking powder and add to wet mixture to make a batter.
Mix batter with milk. Add pecans and dates. Top with whipped cream. Pour boiling syrup into 8x8 pan; drop batter by spoonfuls into syrup, Bake 20 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add baking mix, margarine, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into two 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 325 degrees until brown.
This pie makes it own crust.

title: gold layer cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining 1/3 cup milk and unbeaten eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 round waxed paper lined 8-inch cake pans. Can also be baked in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: meatballs bavarian
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Shape into about 2 1/2 dozen meatballs; coat with flour.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Brown meatballs in bacon grease; remove from pan.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Melt oleo, milk and caramels.
Line bottom of jelly roll pan with Rice Krispies (do not use all of them at once).
On top of Rice Krispies, sprinkle on a few marshmallows, then pour on a portion of melted mixture.
Repeat layers until all ingredients have been used.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Split chiles, cover the bottom of a baking dish.
Sprinkle chiles with the cheese.

In mixing bowl, mix eggs and milk, then add remaining, except green onions; mix well and pour over cheese. Top with green onions, bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until casserole bubbles and puffs up.
Casserole may be refrigerated over night before baking.
Serve with hot rolls, muffins or fresh fruit.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in 2 tablespoons of oleo. Mix together
mayonnaise,
salt,
pepper, egg, milk and soup. Combine this
mixture
with mushroom mixture.
Combine bread, shredded cheese and melted oleo in a separate bowl.
In bottom of a
1 quart
casserole, spread layer of onions and layer of mushrooms. Repeat
until
mushrooms left on top.
Cook for 40 minutes, uncovered, at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add some flour, eggs, applesauce, raisins and dates rolled in flour.
Mix in all spices. If too thick, add water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Pour 2 cups egg nog into the top of a double boiler; add gelatine and stir over the double boiler until dissolved. Remove from heat. Stir in the remaining egg nog and chill until firm. Whip the cream. Fold whipped cream into egg nog mixture. Pour into pie shell and chill until firm.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have an 11 x 17-inch baking dish ready.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until done.
Serve with nacho chips.
Put chips in bottom of bowl.
Add soup and sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: cheese baked chicken
directions: Remove skin and debone, if desired.
Rinse, pat dry and arrange in a 2-quart casserole.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir soup and wine together; pour over. Crush stuffing mix and sprinkle over. Drizzle butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tira mi su(translation "pick-me-up")
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat to the boiling point.
Boil and stir for 1 minute, and then remove form heat.
Place plastic wrap directly onto egg mixture and chill for one hour.
Meanwhile, mix vanilla with cool whip.
Set aside. Separate ladyfingers horizontally in half.
Drizzle with a mixture of the coffee and rum extract.
Arrange half of the ladyfingers in a well greased serving dish.
Set aside.
Remove egg mixture from refrigerator and beat in softened cream cheese with a wire whisk until smooth.
Pour half of this mixture on layer of ladyfingers. Top with half of the cool whip mixture, and then repeat layers. Sprinkle top of dessert with cocoa.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons butter, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 muffin cups. Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup.
Heat in oven until melted.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together well.
Mix oil, eggs, water and sugar well.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Add nuts or raisins.
Grease and flour four (1-pound) coffee cans. Cover with foil.
Place on cook sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: goldwater beans
directions: Cook pinto beans.
Add chilies, taco sauce, tomato sauce and onion.
Cook hamburger until brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve with hard rolls and salad.
I make cornbread.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and chopped onion in a skillet or microwave together.
Add remaining ingredients in any order and mix well. Bake, uncovered, in large casserole dish, for about 2 hours at 350°.
Sometimes I put the bacon and parsley flakes on top.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir once.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 5 to 6 hours.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook beef stew cubes.
When tender, drain off liquid except about 1/2 cup.
Add barbecue sauce to meat and simmer about 30 minutes.
Break up beef with fork before adding sauce.
Serve on rice noodles, if desired.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix well sugar, cocoa, salt, cornstarch and water in a large glass microwave bowl.
Heat 3 minutes; stir.
Heat 3 more minutes on High setting.
Add butter and vanilla; stir.

title: microwave cheesy potato casserole
directions: In bowl, mix together soup, onions, cheese, dill and pepper. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Microwave at High for 9 to 11 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top before serving.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix vinegar, ketchup, soy sauce and brown sugar in saucepan. Mix together in a bowl the juice you drained from the pineapple, cornstarch, garlic salt and ginger.
Add to mixture in saucepan and cook until thickened.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until they are heated through.
Serve on hot rice.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Pour soup and milk mixture over all dry ingredients.
Put in covered dish and store in refrigerator overnight.
Before putting in oven, sprinkle 4 or 5 tablespoons of dressing mix over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: no fuss no hassel italian pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven, sear roast on all sides in hot oil.
Pour jar of Ragu (or one of your choice, make sure it's Italian cooking sauce).
Simmer covered for 2 hours.
Make sure it doesn't cook dry, add more sauce or small amount of water.
But cook slow.

title: cracker pie
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch pie plate.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and sugar until stiff.
Roll the soda crackers until fine; add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Fold the cracker mixture into the beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie plate and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tea cakes
directions: Spoon by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake until slightly browned on bottom at 350°.

title: collard green soup
directions: In 1 quart of water, place the ham bone, Spanish sausages and white bacon.
Let cook for about 1/2 hour.
Add the collard greens and great Northern beans.
Allow to cook over slow heat for 1/2 hour.
Saute the onions and green pepper in bacon fat until onion is transparent.
Add to the greens.
Cut the potatoes in medium size pieces add to the greens.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple-lime punch
directions: Mix 1 package Kool-Aid with 2/3 cup sugar and 1 quart water. Freeze into ice cubes.
Mix 1 package Kool-Aid, 1 quart water, 2/3 cup sugar and pineapple juice together.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up, lime ice cubes and lime sherbet.

title: sugar free pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat oil and eggs with beater until well emulsified. Add sugar subst. and beat until light and fluffy. Add pumpkin then dry ingredients. Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon full onto grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for 20 min. May be frozen after baking. Yield 4 doz.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
You may need a bit more.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: "squash delight"
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.	Dot with butter and cheese.

title: south carolina stewed squash
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: coconut fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in cream of coconut; heat through.
Serve warm over ice cream or with fresh fruit.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn; do not salt.
Bring to a boil sugar, Karo and Jell-O.
Pour over popped corn and shape.
